58template <typename T>
59struct is_complex_t : public std::false_type {};
60
61template <>
62struct is_complex_t<complex64> : public std::true_type {};
63
64template <typename T>
65struct is_complex64_t : public std::false_type {};
66
67template <>
68struct is_complex64_t<complex64> : public std::true_type {};

70template <typename OperandT>
71StatusOr<std::unique_ptr<Literal>> Compare(const Shape& shape, HloOpcode opcode,
72 const Literal& lhs_literal,
73 const Literal& rhs_literal) {
74 std::function<bool(OperandT, OperandT)> compare_op;
75 switch (opcode) {
76 case HloOpcode::kEq:
77 compare_op = [](OperandT lhs_el, OperandT rhs_el) {
78 return lhs_el == rhs_el;
79 };
80 break;
81 case HloOpcode::kNe:
82 compare_op = [](OperandT lhs_el, OperandT rhs_el) {
83 return lhs_el != rhs_el;
84 };
85 break;
86 case HloOpcode::kGe:
87 compare_op = [](OperandT lhs_el, OperandT rhs_el) {
88 return lhs_el >= rhs_el;
89 };
90 break;
91 case HloOpcode::kGt:
92 compare_op = [](OperandT lhs_el, OperandT rhs_el) {
93 return lhs_el > rhs_el;
94 };
95 break;
96 case HloOpcode::kLe:
97 compare_op = [](OperandT lhs_el, OperandT rhs_el) {
98 return lhs_el <= rhs_el;
99 };
100 break;
101 case HloOpcode::kLt:
102 compare_op = [](OperandT lhs_el, OperandT rhs_el) {
103 return lhs_el < rhs_el;
104 };
105 break;
106 default:
107 LOG(FATAL) << "unhandled HLO opcode for conversion to Comparison: "
108 << HloOpcodeString(opcode);
109 }
110
111 auto result = Literal::CreateFromShape(shape);
112 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(result->Populate<bool>([&](ArraySlice<int64> multi_index) {
113 return compare_op(lhs_literal.Get<OperandT>(multi_index),
114 rhs_literal.Get<OperandT>(multi_index));
115 }));
116
117 return std::move(result);
118}
119
120template <>
121StatusOr<std::unique_ptr<Literal>> Compare<complex64>(
122 const Shape& shape, HloOpcode opcode, const Literal& lhs_literal,
123 const Literal& rhs_literal) {
124 std::function<bool(complex64, complex64)> compare_op;
125 switch (opcode) {
126 case HloOpcode::kEq:
127 compare_op = [](complex64 lhs_el, complex64 rhs_el) {
128 return lhs_el == rhs_el;
129 };
130 break;
131 case HloOpcode::kNe:
132 compare_op = [](complex64 lhs_el, complex64 rhs_el) {
133 return lhs_el != rhs_el;
134 };
135 break;
136 default:
137 LOG(FATAL) << "unhandled HLO opcode for conversion to Comparison: "
138 << HloOpcodeString(opcode);
139 }
140
141 auto result = Literal::CreateFromShape(shape);
142 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(result->Populate<bool>([&](ArraySlice<int64> multi_index) {
143 return compare_op(lhs_literal.Get<complex64>(multi_index),
144 rhs_literal.Get<complex64>(multi_index));
145 }));
146
147 return std::move(result);
148}
149
150template <typename ReturnT, typename NativeT>
151StatusOr<std::unique_ptr<Literal>> ElementWiseUnaryOpImpl(
152 HloInstruction* instruction,
153 const std::function<ReturnT(NativeT)>& unary_op,
154 const Literal& operand_literal) {
155 const auto shape = instruction->shape();
156 const auto* operand = instruction->operand(0);
157
158 // TODO(b/35950897, b/27796129): add DCHECK back once implicit broadcast is
159 // removed.
160 if (!ShapeUtil::SameDimensions(shape, operand->shape())) {
161 return Unimplemented(
162 "Implicit broadcasting is currently unsupported in HLO evaluator "
163 "Shape Mismatch: %s vs %s",
164 ShapeUtil::HumanString(shape).c_str(),
165 ShapeUtil::HumanString(operand->shape()).c_str());
166 }
167
168 auto result = Literal::CreateFromShape(shape);
169
170 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
171 result->Populate<ReturnT>([&](ArraySlice<int64> multi_index) {
172 return unary_op(operand_literal.Get<NativeT>(multi_index));
173 }));
174 return std::move(result);
175}
176
177// For one particular placement of a window in a base shape (the placement is
178// represented as `window_count_index`), iterates inside the window. Translates
179// the window index into base index. If the base index is within bound, call `f`
180// with the base index.
181void IterateThroughWindow(
182 const Shape& window_shape, const Window& window, const Shape& base_shape,
183 const ArraySlice<int64>& window_count_index,
184 const std::function<void(const std::vector<int64>&)>& f) {
185 const int64 rank = ShapeUtil::Rank(base_shape);
186 DimensionVector window_index(rank);
187 std::fill(window_index.begin(), window_index.end(), 0);
188 do {
189 std::vector<int64> base_index(rank);
190 bool out_of_bound = false;
191 for (int64 i = 0; i < rank; ++i) {
192 base_index[i] = window_count_index[i] * window.dimensions(i).stride() +
193 window_index[i] - window.dimensions(i).padding_low();
194 if (base_index[i] < 0 || base_index[i] >= base_shape.dimensions(i)) {
195 out_of_bound = true;
196 break;
197 }
198 }
199 if (!out_of_bound) {
200 f(base_index);
201 }
202 } while (IndexUtil::BumpIndices(window_shape, &window_index));
203}
204
205// Creates a vector of multipliers which can be used to create a linear index
206// into shape.
207//
208// Given the multidimensional index {i1, ..., iN} and
209// M = MakeDimMultipliers(shape), the corresponding linear index LI is simply
210//
211// LI = i1 * M[1] + i2 * M[2] + ... + iN * M[N].
212//
213// This lets you calculate LI given the multidimensional indices in any order.
214DimensionVector MakeDimMultipliers(const Shape& shape) {
215 DimensionVector v(ShapeUtil::Rank(shape));
216 int64 scale = 1;
217 for (auto dim : LayoutUtil::MinorToMajor(shape)) {
218 v[dim] = scale;
219 scale *= shape.dimensions(dim);
220 }
221 return v;
222}
223
224} // namespace

226template <typename ReturnT, typename ElementwiseT>
227class HloEvaluator::TypedVisitor : public DfsHloVisitorWithDefault {
228 public:
229 explicit TypedVisitor(HloEvaluator* p) : parent_(p) {}
230
231 // The following higher-order functions convert a function with ElementwiseT
232 // to a function with ReturnT.
233 std::function<ReturnT(ReturnT)> ConvertUnaryFunction(
234 const std::function<ElementwiseT(ElementwiseT)>& unary_op) {
235 return [&unary_op](ReturnT arg) {
236 return static_cast<ReturnT>(unary_op(static_cast<ElementwiseT>(arg)));
237 };
238 }
239 std::function<ReturnT(ReturnT, ReturnT)> ConvertBinaryFunction(
240 const std::function<ElementwiseT(ElementwiseT, ElementwiseT)>&
241 binary_op) {
242 return [&binary_op](ReturnT arg1, ReturnT arg2) {
243 return static_cast<ReturnT>(binary_op(static_cast<ElementwiseT>(arg1),
244 static_cast<ElementwiseT>(arg2)));
245 };
246 }
247 std::function<ReturnT(ReturnT, ReturnT, ReturnT)> ConvertTernaryFunction(
248 const std::function<ElementwiseT(ElementwiseT, ElementwiseT,
249 ElementwiseT)>& ternary_op) {
250 return [&ternary_op](ReturnT arg1, ReturnT arg2, ReturnT arg3) {
251 return static_cast<ReturnT>(ternary_op(static_cast<ElementwiseT>(arg1),
252 static_cast<ElementwiseT>(arg2),
253 static_cast<ElementwiseT>(arg3)));
254 };
255 }
256
257 Status DefaultAction(HloInstruction* hlo_instruction) override {
258 return Unimplemented("unhandled HLO ops for HloEvaluator: %s.",
259 HloOpcodeString(hlo_instruction->opcode()).c_str());
260 }

262 // TODO(b/35950897): many of the stl functions used in the handlers are not
263 // overloaded for every XLA primitive types.
264
265 template <typename NativeT,
266 typename std::enable_if<std::is_unsigned<NativeT>::value>::type* =
267 nullptr>
268 Status HandleAbs(HloInstruction* abs) {
269 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(parent_->evaluated_[abs],
270 ElementWiseUnaryOp(abs, [](NativeT elem_operand) {
271 return elem_operand;
272 }));
273 return Status::OK();
274 }
275
276 template <
277 typename NativeT,
278 typename std::enable_if<std::is_signed<NativeT>::value>::type* = nullptr>
279 Status HandleAbs(HloInstruction* abs) {
280 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(parent_->evaluated_[abs],
281 ElementWiseUnaryOp(abs, [](NativeT elem_operand) {
282 return std::abs(elem_operand);
283 }));
284 return Status::OK();
285 }
286
287 template <
288 typename NativeT,
289 typename std::enable_if<is_complex64_t<NativeT>::value>::type* = nullptr>
290 Status HandleAbs(HloInstruction* abs) {
291 const Literal& operand_literal =
292 parent_->GetEvaluatedLiteralFor(abs->operand(0));
293 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(
294 parent_->evaluated_[abs],
295 (ElementWiseUnaryOpImpl<float, NativeT>(
296 abs, [](NativeT elem_operand) { return std::abs(elem_operand); },
297 operand_literal)));
298
299 return Status::OK();
300 }
301
302 Status HandleAbs(HloInstruction* abs) override {
303 // If the operand is of C64 type, the return type of abs will be F32.
304 // However, ElementwiseT would still be the return type, F32, and thus
305 // specifying the ElementwiseT explicitly as C64 is needed below.
306 if (abs->operand(0)->shape().element_type() == C64) {
307 return HandleAbs<complex64>(abs);
308 }
309 return HandleAbs<ElementwiseT>(abs);
310 }

312 template <
313 typename NativeT,
314 typename std::enable_if<!is_complex_t<NativeT>::value>::type* = nullptr>
315 Status HandleRound(HloInstruction* round) {
316 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(
317 parent_->evaluated_[round],
318 ElementWiseUnaryOp(round, [](ElementwiseT elem_operand) {
319 return std::round(elem_operand);
320 }));
321 return Status::OK();
322 }
323
324 template <
325 typename NativeT,
326 typename std::enable_if<is_complex_t<NativeT>::value>::type* = nullptr>
327 Status HandleRound(HloInstruction* round) {
328 return InvalidArgument("Unsupported type for Round");
329 }
330
331 Status HandleRound(HloInstruction* round) override {
332 return HandleRound<ReturnT>(round);
333 }
334
335 Status HandleBroadcast(HloInstruction* broadcast) override {
336 parent_->evaluated_[broadcast] =
337 Literal::CreateFromShape(broadcast->shape());
338 auto output = parent_->evaluated_[broadcast].get();
339 const Literal& operand_to_broadcast =
340 parent_->GetEvaluatedLiteralFor(broadcast->operand(0));
341 std::vector<int64> broadcast_indices(
342 ShapeUtil::Rank(broadcast->operand(0)->shape()), 0);
343
344 TF_RET_CHECK(broadcast->dimensions().size() ==
345 ShapeUtil::Rank(operand_to_broadcast.shape()))
346 << "broadcast dimensions is of size: " << broadcast->dimensions().size()
347 << " and rank of operand_to_broadcast is: "
348 << ShapeUtil::Rank(operand_to_broadcast.shape());
349 // Checks that operand's dimensions are the same as the broadcast's
350 // dimensions along the dimensions to be broadcasted.
351 for (int64 i = 0; i < broadcast->dimensions().size(); ++i) {
352 TF_RET_CHECK(broadcast->shape().dimensions(broadcast->dimensions(i)) ==
353 operand_to_broadcast.shape().dimensions(i));
354 }
355
356 return output->Populate<ReturnT>([&](ArraySlice<int64> multi_index) {
357 for (int64 i = 0; i < broadcast->dimensions().size(); ++i) {
358 broadcast_indices[i] = multi_index[broadcast->dimensions(i)];
359 }
360 return operand_to_broadcast.Get<ReturnT>(broadcast_indices);
361 });
362 }

375 template <
376 typename NativeT,
377 typename std::enable_if<is_complex_t<NativeT>::value>::type* = nullptr>
378 Status HandleCeil(HloInstruction* ceil) {
379 return InvalidArgument("Unsupported type for Ceil");
380 }

382 Status HandleCeil(HloInstruction* ceil) override {
383 return HandleCeil<ReturnT>(ceil);
384 }
385
386 Status HandleConvert(HloInstruction* convert) override {
387 const HloInstruction* operand = convert->operand(0);
388 TF_RET_CHECK(ShapeUtil::SameDimensions(operand->shape(), convert->shape()));
389 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(std::unique_ptr<Literal> result,
390 parent_->GetEvaluatedLiteralFor(operand).Convert(
391 convert->shape().element_type()));
392
393 if (LayoutUtil::LayoutsInShapesEqual(result->shape(), convert->shape())) {
394 parent_->evaluated_[convert] = std::move(result);
395 } else {
396 parent_->evaluated_[convert] =
397 result->Relayout(convert->shape().layout());
398 }
399 return Status::OK();
400 }
401
402 Status HandleBitcastConvert(HloInstruction* convert) override {
403 const HloInstruction* operand = convert->operand(0);
404 TF_RET_CHECK(ShapeUtil::SameDimensions(operand->shape(), convert->shape()));
405 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(std::unique_ptr<Literal> result,
406 parent_->GetEvaluatedLiteralFor(operand).BitcastConvert(
407 convert->shape().element_type()));
408
409 if (LayoutUtil::LayoutsInShapesEqual(result->shape(), convert->shape())) {
410 parent_->evaluated_[convert] = std::move(result);
411 } else {
412 parent_->evaluated_[convert] =
413 result->Relayout(convert->shape().layout());
414 }
415 return Status::OK();
416 }

501 template <typename NativeT,
502 typename std::enable_if<
503 std::is_signed<NativeT>::value &&
504 !std::is_floating_point<NativeT>::value>::type* = nullptr>
505 Status HandleNegate(HloInstruction* negate) {
506 using type = typename std::make_unsigned<NativeT>::type;
507 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(
508 parent_->evaluated_[negate],
509 ElementWiseUnaryOp(negate, [](ElementwiseT elem_operand) {
510 return NativeT(-type(elem_operand));
511 }));
512 return Status::OK();
513 }

520 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(
521 parent_->evaluated_[negate],

523 negate, [](ElementwiseT elem_operand) { return -elem_operand; }));
524 return Status::OK();

531 template <
532 typename NativeT,
533 typename std::enable_if<!is_complex_t<NativeT>::value>::type* = nullptr>
534 Status HandleSign(HloInstruction* sign) {
535 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(parent_->evaluated_[sign],
536 ElementWiseUnaryOp(sign, [](ElementwiseT elem_operand) {
537 return (ElementwiseT(0) < elem_operand) -
538 (elem_operand < ElementwiseT(0));
539 }));
540 return Status::OK();
541 }
542
543 template <
544 typename NativeT,
545 typename std::enable_if<is_complex_t<NativeT>::value>::type* = nullptr>
546 Status HandleSign(HloInstruction* sign) {
547 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(parent_->evaluated_[sign],
548 ElementWiseUnaryOp(sign, [](ElementwiseT elem_operand) {
549 auto abs_val = std::abs(elem_operand);
550 return 0 == abs_val ? ElementwiseT(0)
551 : elem_operand / abs_val;
552 }));
553 return Status::OK();
554 }
555
556 Status HandleSign(HloInstruction* sign) override {
557 return HandleSign<ReturnT>(sign);
558 }

661 }

820 template <typename NativeT,

825 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(
826 parent_->evaluated_[shl],
827 ElementWiseBinaryOp(shl, [](NativeT lhs_elem, NativeT rhs_elem) {
828 return IsShiftOutOfBounds<NativeT>(rhs_elem) ? 0
829 : (lhs_elem << rhs_elem);
830 }));
831 return Status::OK();

845 template <typename NativeT,
846 typename std::enable_if<
847 std::is_integral<NativeT>::value &&
848 !std::is_same<NativeT, bool>::value>::type* = nullptr>
849 Status HandleShiftRightArithmetic(HloInstruction* shr) {
850 typedef typename std::make_signed<NativeT>::type SignedT;
851 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(
852 parent_->evaluated_[shr],
853 ElementWiseBinaryOp(shr, [](NativeT lhs_elem, NativeT rhs_elem) {
854 SignedT lhs_signed = static_cast<SignedT>(lhs_elem);
855 if (IsShiftOutOfBounds<NativeT>(rhs_elem)) {
856 return lhs_signed < 0 ? static_cast<SignedT>(-1) : 0;
857 } else {
858 return lhs_signed >> rhs_elem;
859 }
860 }));
861 return Status::OK();
862 }

876 template <typename NativeT,
877 typename std::enable_if<
878 std::is_integral<NativeT>::value &&
879 !std::is_same<NativeT, bool>::value>::type* = nullptr>
880 Status HandleShiftRightLogical(HloInstruction* shr) {
881 typedef typename std::make_unsigned<NativeT>::type UnsignedT;
882 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(
883 parent_->evaluated_[shr],
884 ElementWiseBinaryOp(shr, [](NativeT lhs_elem, NativeT rhs_elem) {
885 // If shift amount is greater than the number of bits, then return 0.
886 if (IsShiftOutOfBounds<NativeT>(rhs_elem)) {
887 return static_cast<NativeT>(0);
888 }
889 return static_cast<NativeT>(static_cast<UnsignedT>(lhs_elem) >>
890 rhs_elem);
891 }));
892 return Status::OK();
893 }

933 Status HandleSelect(HloInstruction* select) override {
934 CHECK(!ShapeUtil::IsScalar(select->operand(0)->shape()));
935 CHECK(!ShapeUtil::IsTuple(select->shape()));
936 std::function<ReturnT(bool, ReturnT, ReturnT)> select_op =
937 [](bool pred, ReturnT on_true, ReturnT on_false) {
938 if (pred) {
939 return on_true;
940 }
941 return on_false;

948 Status HandleReverse(HloInstruction* reverse) override {
949 const auto result_shape = reverse->shape();
950 const auto reverse_dimensions = reverse->dimensions();
951
952 auto operand = reverse->operand(0);
953 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(auto inferred_return_shape,
954 ShapeInference::InferReverseShape(operand->shape(),
955 reverse_dimensions));
956
957 TF_RET_CHECK(ShapeUtil::Compatible(result_shape, inferred_return_shape))
958 << "return shape set to: " << ShapeUtil::HumanString(result_shape)
959 << " but is inferred to be: "
960 << ShapeUtil::HumanString(inferred_return_shape);
961
962 const Literal& operand_literal = parent_->GetEvaluatedLiteralFor(operand);
963 auto result = Literal::CreateFromShape(result_shape);
964
965 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
966 result->Populate<ReturnT>([&](ArraySlice<int64> out_index) {
967 std::vector<int64> from_index(out_index.begin(), out_index.end());
968 for (const int64 dim : reverse_dimensions) {
969 from_index[dim] = result_shape.dimensions(dim) - 1 - out_index[dim];
970 }
971 return operand_literal.Get<ReturnT>(from_index);
972 }));
973
974 parent_->evaluated_[reverse] = std::move(result);
975 return Status::OK();
976 }
977
978 Status HandleConvolution(HloInstruction* conv) override {
979 auto lhs = conv->operand(0);
980 auto rhs = conv->operand(1);
981 const auto& window = conv->window();
982 const Shape& result_shape = conv->shape();
983 const Shape& lhs_shape = lhs->shape();
984 const Shape& rhs_shape = rhs->shape();
985
986 TF_CHECK_OK(ShapeUtil::ValidateShape(lhs_shape));
987 TF_CHECK_OK(ShapeUtil::ValidateShape(rhs_shape));
988 CHECK(ShapeUtil::IsArray(lhs_shape));
989 CHECK(ShapeUtil::IsArray(rhs_shape));
990 CHECK(ShapeUtil::SameElementType(lhs_shape, rhs_shape));
991 CHECK(ShapeUtil::SameElementType(lhs_shape, result_shape));
992
993 const auto& dnums = conv->convolution_dimension_numbers();
994 const int64 num_spatial_dims = dnums.output_spatial_dimensions_size();
995 CHECK_EQ(num_spatial_dims, dnums.input_spatial_dimensions_size());
996 CHECK_EQ(num_spatial_dims, dnums.kernel_spatial_dimensions_size());
997 CHECK_GE(num_spatial_dims, 0);
998 CHECK_EQ(window.dimensions_size(), num_spatial_dims);
999
1000 const auto lhs_rank = ShapeUtil::Rank(lhs_shape);
1001 const auto rhs_rank = ShapeUtil::Rank(rhs_shape);
1002
1003 CHECK_EQ(num_spatial_dims + 2, lhs_rank);
1004 CHECK_EQ(num_spatial_dims + 2, rhs_rank);
1005
1006 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(auto inferred_return_shape,
1007 ShapeInference::InferConvolveShape(lhs_shape, rhs_shape,
1008 window, dnums));
1009 CHECK(ShapeUtil::Compatible(result_shape, inferred_return_shape))
1010 << "return shape set to: " << ShapeUtil::HumanString(result_shape)
1011 << " but is inferred to be: "
1012 << ShapeUtil::HumanString(inferred_return_shape);
1013
1014 const Literal& lhs_literal = parent_->GetEvaluatedLiteralFor(lhs);
1015 const Literal& rhs_literal = parent_->GetEvaluatedLiteralFor(rhs);
1016
1017 std::vector<int64> window_dimension_sizes;
1018 for (auto i : dnums.kernel_spatial_dimensions()) {
1019 window_dimension_sizes.push_back(ShapeUtil::GetDimension(rhs_shape, i));
1020 }
1021
1022 const Shape& window_shape =
1023 ShapeUtil::MakeShape(rhs_shape.element_type(), window_dimension_sizes);
1024
1025 DimensionVector lhs_dim_multipliers = MakeDimMultipliers(lhs_shape);
1026 DimensionVector rhs_dim_multipliers = MakeDimMultipliers(rhs_shape);
1027
1028 auto lhs_literal_data = lhs_literal.data<ReturnT>();
1029 auto rhs_literal_data = rhs_literal.data<ReturnT>();
1030
1031 auto func = [&window_shape, &dnums, &lhs_shape, &rhs_shape, &window,
1032 &lhs_dim_multipliers, &rhs_dim_multipliers, lhs_literal_data,
1033 rhs_literal_data](ArraySlice<int64> out_index) {
1034 // Dimension number applicable for input (lhs).
1035 const int64 input_batch_dim = dnums.input_batch_dimension();
1036 const int64 input_z_dim = dnums.input_feature_dimension();
1037 // Dimension number applicable for kernel (rhs).
1038 const int64 kernel_input_z_dim = dnums.kernel_input_feature_dimension();
1039 const int64 kernel_output_z_dim = dnums.kernel_output_feature_dimension();
1040 // Dimension number applicable for output.
1041 const int64 output_batch_dim = dnums.output_batch_dimension();
1042 const int64 output_z_dim = dnums.output_feature_dimension();
1043
1044 const int64 z_size = ShapeUtil::GetDimension(lhs_shape, input_z_dim);
1045
1046 ElementwiseT result_val = static_cast<ElementwiseT>(0);
1047 DimensionVector rhs_spatial_index(dnums.kernel_spatial_dimensions_size(),
1048 0);
1049
1050 // Convolve input feature with kernel.
1051 do {
1052 for (int64 iz = 0; iz < z_size; ++iz) {
1053 int64 lhs_linear_index = 0;
1054 lhs_linear_index += out_index[output_batch_dim] *
1055 lhs_dim_multipliers[input_batch_dim];
1056 lhs_linear_index += iz * lhs_dim_multipliers[input_z_dim];
1057
1058 int64 rhs_linear_index = 0;
1059 rhs_linear_index += out_index[output_z_dim] *
1060 rhs_dim_multipliers[kernel_output_z_dim];
1061 rhs_linear_index += iz * rhs_dim_multipliers[kernel_input_z_dim];
1062
1063 // Find corresponding spatial dimension index for input (lhs).
1064 for (int64 ki = 0; ki < rhs_spatial_index.size(); ++ki) {
1065 // Spatial dimension number for input (lhs) and output.
1066 const int64 input_spatial_dim = dnums.input_spatial_dimensions(ki);
1067 const int64 output_spatial_dim =
1068 dnums.output_spatial_dimensions(ki);
1069
1070 // Calculate lhs (input) index without taking base dilation into
1071 // account.
1072 const auto& window_dim = window.dimensions(ki);
1073 const int64 undilated_index =
1074 out_index[output_spatial_dim] * window_dim.stride() -
1075 window_dim.padding_low() +
1076 rhs_spatial_index[ki] * window_dim.window_dilation();
1077 // Skip if the lhs (input) index is to be dilated. As an
1078 // optimization, skip this mod if there's no dilation.
1079 if (window_dim.base_dilation() > 1 &&
1080 undilated_index % window_dim.base_dilation() != 0) {
1081 goto cnt;
1082 }
1083
1084 // Calculate the actual lhs (input) index after dilation. As an
1085 // optimization, skip this integer divide if there's no dilation.
1086 int64 lhs_spatial_index;
1087 if (window_dim.base_dilation() > 1) {
1088 lhs_spatial_index = undilated_index / window_dim.base_dilation();
1089 } else {
1090 lhs_spatial_index = undilated_index;
1091 }
1092 lhs_linear_index +=
1093 lhs_spatial_index * lhs_dim_multipliers[input_spatial_dim];
1094
1095 // Skip if input index is not in bounds.
1096 if (!(lhs_spatial_index >= 0 &&
1097 lhs_spatial_index <
1098 lhs_shape.dimensions(input_spatial_dim))) {
1099 goto cnt;
1100 }
1101
1102 rhs_linear_index +=
1103 (window_dim.window_reversal()
1104 ? ((window_dim.size() - 1) - rhs_spatial_index[ki])
1105 : rhs_spatial_index[ki]) *
1106 rhs_dim_multipliers[dnums.kernel_spatial_dimensions(ki)];
1107 }
1108
1109 result_val +=
1110 static_cast<ElementwiseT>(lhs_literal_data[lhs_linear_index]) *
1111 static_cast<ElementwiseT>(rhs_literal_data[rhs_linear_index]);
1112 }
1113 cnt : {}
1114 } while (IndexUtil::BumpIndices(window_shape, &rhs_spatial_index));
1115
1116 return static_cast<ReturnT>(result_val);
1117 };
1118
1119 auto result = Literal::CreateFromShape(result_shape);
1120 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(result->PopulateParallel<ReturnT>(func));
1121
1122 parent_->evaluated_[conv] = std::move(result);
1123 return Status::OK();
1124 }
1125
1126 Status HandleDot(HloInstruction* dot) override {
1127 auto lhs = dot->operand(0);
1128 auto rhs = dot->operand(1);
1129 CHECK(ShapeUtil::IsArray(dot->shape()));
1130 CHECK(ShapeUtil::IsArray(lhs->shape()));
1131 CHECK(ShapeUtil::IsArray(rhs->shape()));
1132
1133 const auto& dnums = dot->dot_dimension_numbers();
1134
1135 const auto lhs_rank = ShapeUtil::Rank(lhs->shape());
1136 const auto rhs_rank = ShapeUtil::Rank(rhs->shape());
1137
1138 CHECK(ShapeUtil::SameElementType(lhs->shape(), rhs->shape()));
1139 CHECK(ShapeUtil::SameElementType(lhs->shape(), dot->shape()));
1140
1141 // There must be 1 and only 1 Contracting dimension for lhs and rhs.
1142 CHECK_EQ(dnums.lhs_contracting_dimensions_size(), 1);
1143 CHECK_EQ(dnums.rhs_contracting_dimensions_size(), 1);
1144 const int64 lhs_contracting_dimension = dnums.lhs_contracting_dimensions(0);
1145 const int64 rhs_contracting_dimension = dnums.rhs_contracting_dimensions(0);
1146 // Contracted dimension sizes must be the same.
1147 CHECK_EQ(lhs->shape().dimensions(lhs_contracting_dimension),
1148 rhs->shape().dimensions(rhs_contracting_dimension))
1149 << "lhs contracted dimension: "
1150 << lhs->shape().dimensions(lhs_contracting_dimension)
1151 << " rhs contracted dimension: "
1152 << rhs->shape().dimensions(rhs_contracting_dimension);
1153 const int64 contracted_dimension_size =
1154 lhs->shape().dimensions(lhs_contracting_dimension);
1155
1156 const Literal& lhs_literal = parent_->GetEvaluatedLiteralFor(lhs);
1157 const Literal& rhs_literal = parent_->GetEvaluatedLiteralFor(rhs);
1158
1159 auto result = Literal::CreateFromShape(dot->shape());
1160
1161 CHECK_EQ(dnums.lhs_batch_dimensions_size(),
1162 dnums.rhs_batch_dimensions_size());
1163
1164 std::vector<int64> lhs_non_contracting_dims;
1165 for (int64 i = 0; i < lhs_rank; i++) {
1166 if (i != lhs_contracting_dimension) {
1167 lhs_non_contracting_dims.push_back(i);
1168 }
1169 }
1170
1171 std::vector<int64> rhs_non_batch_non_contracting_dims;
1172 FlatSet<int64> batch_dims_set(dnums.rhs_batch_dimensions().begin(),
1173 dnums.rhs_batch_dimensions().end());
1174 for (int64 i = 0; i < rhs_rank; i++) {
1175 if (i != rhs_contracting_dimension && batch_dims_set.count(i) == 0) {
1176 rhs_non_batch_non_contracting_dims.push_back(i);
1177 }
1178 }
1179
1180 const int64 batch_dim_size = dnums.lhs_batch_dimensions_size();
1181 const int64 lhs_non_contracting_size = lhs_non_contracting_dims.size();
1182
1183 DimensionVector lhs_index(lhs_rank);
1184 DimensionVector rhs_index(rhs_rank);
1185 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
1186 result->Populate<ReturnT>([&](ArraySlice<int64> result_index) {
1187 ElementwiseT result_val = static_cast<ElementwiseT>(0);
1188
1189 // Find the corresponding non-contracting indices for lhs and rhs.
1190 //
1191 // For `result_index`, its batch dimension, if exists, will be at the
1192 // same dimension as the batch dimension of lhs and rhs. More
1193 // specifically:
1194 // - For lhs, the non-contracting dimensions, including the batch
1195 // dimension have the same index as the `result_index`.
1196 // - For rhs, the batch dimension is set seperately from other
1197 // non-contracting dimensions, since these other non-contracting
1198 // dimensions in rhs follow the non-contracting dimensions of lhs in
1199 // the resulting index.
1200 //
1201 // As an example, for a resulting index:
1202 // result_index [result_batch, result_x, result_y]
1203 // the effecting lhs and rhs indices are:
1204 // lhs [result_batch, lhs_non_contracting_dim, contracting_dim
1205 // rhs [result_batch, contracting_dim, rhs_non_contracting_dim]
1206 // `result_x` is only affected by the lhs_non_contracting_dim and
1207 // likewise `result_y` only depends on rhs_non_contracting_dim.
1208 //
1209 // so we can look up the lhs and rhs indices by:
1210 //
1211 // lhs:
1212 // batch index is the same as `result_batch`.
1213 // non-contracting dimension is the same as
1214 // result_index[lhs_non_contracting_dim]
1215 // rhs:
1216 // batch index: the same as `result_batch`.
1217 // non-contracting dimension index: *not* the same as
1218 // result_index[rhs_non_contractng_dim], since the
1219 // non-contracting dimensions of lhs are included in the
1220 // result_index first. Instead, the non_contracting_dim of rhs must
1221 // be calculated as following:
1222 // lhs_non_contracting_dimensions_size +
1223 // (rhs_non_batch_non_contracting_dim - batch_dim_size) - 1
1224 //
1225 // Note that (rhs_non_batch_contracting_dim - batch_dim_size) is
1226 // the index offset to the result_index that only depends on
1227 // the non_batch and non-contracting dimensions of rhs. -1 at the
1228 // end translates size to index.
1229 for (auto i : lhs_non_contracting_dims) {
1230 lhs_index[i] = result_index[i];
1231 }
1232 for (auto i : dnums.rhs_batch_dimensions()) {
1233 rhs_index[i] = result_index[i];
1234 }
1235 for (auto i : rhs_non_batch_non_contracting_dims) {
1236 const int64 rhs_non_batch_non_contracting_dim =
1237 lhs_non_contracting_size + (i - batch_dim_size) - 1;
1238 rhs_index[i] = result_index[rhs_non_batch_non_contracting_dim];
1239 }
1240
1241 // Accumulates resulting product along the contracted dimension.
1242 for (int64 i = 0; i < contracted_dimension_size; ++i) {
1243 lhs_index[lhs_contracting_dimension] = i;
1244 rhs_index[rhs_contracting_dimension] = i;
1245
1246 result_val +=
1247 static_cast<ElementwiseT>(lhs_literal.Get<ReturnT>(lhs_index)) *
1248 static_cast<ElementwiseT>(rhs_literal.Get<ReturnT>(rhs_index));
1249 }
1250
1251 return static_cast<ReturnT>(result_val);
1252 }));
1253
1254 parent_->evaluated_[dot] = std::move(result);
1255 return Status::OK();
1256 }
1257
1258 Status HandlePad(HloInstruction* pad) override {
1259 CHECK(!ShapeUtil::IsTuple(pad->operand(0)->shape()));
1260 // Padding value must be scalar.
1261 CHECK(ShapeUtil::IsScalar(pad->operand(1)->shape()));
1262 CHECK_EQ(ShapeUtil::Rank(pad->operand(0)->shape()),
1263 pad->padding_config().dimensions_size());
1264
1265 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(auto inferred_return_shape,
1266 ShapeInference::InferPadShape(
1267 /*operand_shape=*/pad->operand(0)->shape(),
1268 /*padding_value_shape=*/pad->operand(1)->shape(),
1269 /*padding_config=*/pad->padding_config()));
1270 CHECK(ShapeUtil::Compatible(pad->shape(), inferred_return_shape))
1271 << "return shape is set to: " << ShapeUtil::HumanString(pad->shape())
1272 << "but is inferred to be: "
1273 << ShapeUtil::HumanString(inferred_return_shape);
1274
1275 // Create new HLO of padded shape with padding value.
1276 ReturnT scalar =
1277 parent_->GetEvaluatedLiteralFor(pad->operand(1)).Get<ReturnT>({});
1278 auto result = Literal::CreateFromShape(pad->shape());
1279 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(result->Populate<ReturnT>(
1280 [&scalar](ArraySlice<int64> multi_index) { return scalar; }));
1281
1282 const Literal& evaluated_operand =
1283 parent_->GetEvaluatedLiteralFor(pad->operand(0));
1284
1285 std::vector<int64> input_index(ShapeUtil::Rank(evaluated_operand.shape()),
1286 0);
1287 std::vector<int64> target_index(ShapeUtil::Rank(result->shape()), 0);
1288
1289 // Loop through each element of the operand, assign them to the
1290 // corresponding index of the resulting padded literal.
1291 const PaddingConfig& pad_config = pad->padding_config();
1292
1293 auto func = [&](ArraySlice<int64> input_index) {
1294 for (auto i = 0; i < input_index.size(); ++i) {
1295 // Interior padding occurs logically before edge padding, so in the case
1296 // of negative edge padding elements are removed from the
1297 // interior-padded operand.
1298 target_index[i] =
1299 pad_config.dimensions(i).edge_padding_low() +
1300 input_index[i] * (pad_config.dimensions(i).interior_padding() + 1);
1301
1302 // Account for negative low and high padding: skip assignment if the
1303 // any target index is out of range.
1304 if (!(target_index[i] >= 0 &&
1305 target_index[i] < pad->shape().dimensions(i))) {
1306 return true;
1307 }
1308 }
1309 result->Set<ReturnT>(target_index,
1310 evaluated_operand.Get<ReturnT>(input_index));
1311 return true;
1312 };
1313
1314 std::vector<int64> zero_base(evaluated_operand.shape().dimensions_size(),
1315 0);
1316 std::vector<int64> step(evaluated_operand.shape().dimensions_size(), 1);
1317
1318 ShapeUtil::ForEachIndex(
1319 evaluated_operand.shape(), zero_base,
1320 AsInt64Slice(evaluated_operand.shape().dimensions()), step, func);
1321
1322 parent_->evaluated_[pad] = std::move(result);
1323 return Status::OK();
1324 }
1325
1326 Status HandleDynamicSlice(HloInstruction* dynamic_slice) override {
1327 auto operand = dynamic_slice->operand(0);
1328 auto start_indices = dynamic_slice->operand(1);
1329 auto result_shape = dynamic_slice->shape();
1330 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(auto inferred_return_shape,
1331 ShapeInference::InferDynamicSliceShape(
1332 operand->shape(), start_indices->shape(),
1333 dynamic_slice->dynamic_slice_sizes()));
1334 TF_RET_CHECK(ShapeUtil::Compatible(result_shape, inferred_return_shape))
1335 << "return shape is set to: " << ShapeUtil::HumanString(result_shape)
1336 << "but is inferred to be: "
1337 << ShapeUtil::HumanString(inferred_return_shape);
1338 TF_RET_CHECK(
1339 primitive_util::IsIntegralType(start_indices->shape().element_type()));
1340
1341 const Literal& operand_literal = parent_->GetEvaluatedLiteralFor(operand);
1342 const Literal& start_indices_literal =
1343 parent_->GetEvaluatedLiteralFor(start_indices);
1344
1345 switch (start_indices->shape().element_type()) {
1346 case S32: {
1347 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(
1348 parent_->evaluated_[dynamic_slice],
1349 DynamicSlice<int32>(operand_literal, start_indices_literal,
1350 result_shape));
1351 } break;
1352 case S64: {
1353 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(
1354 parent_->evaluated_[dynamic_slice],
1355 DynamicSlice<int64>(operand_literal, start_indices_literal,
1356 result_shape));
1357 } break;
1358 case U32: {
1359 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(
1360 parent_->evaluated_[dynamic_slice],
1361 DynamicSlice<uint32>(operand_literal, start_indices_literal,
1362 result_shape));
1363 } break;
1364 case U64: {
1365 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(
1366 parent_->evaluated_[dynamic_slice],
1367 DynamicSlice<uint64>(operand_literal, start_indices_literal,
1368 result_shape));
1369 } break;
1370 default:
1371 LOG(FATAL) << "HandleDynamicSlice: unhandled primitive type for "
1372 "start_indices: "
1373 << PrimitiveType_Name(start_indices->shape().element_type());
1374 }
1375
1376 return Status::OK();
1377 }
1378
1379 Status HandleDynamicUpdateSlice(
1380 HloInstruction* dynamic_update_slice) override {
1381 auto operand = dynamic_update_slice->operand(0);
1382 auto update = dynamic_update_slice->operand(1);
1383 auto start_indices = dynamic_update_slice->operand(2);
1384 auto result_shape = dynamic_update_slice->shape();
1385 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(
1386 auto inferred_return_shape,
1387 ShapeInference::InferDynamicUpdateSliceShape(
1388 operand->shape(), update->shape(), start_indices->shape()));
1389 TF_RET_CHECK(ShapeUtil::Compatible(result_shape, inferred_return_shape))
1390 << "return shape is set to: " << ShapeUtil::HumanString(result_shape)
1391 << "but is inferred to be: "
1392 << ShapeUtil::HumanString(inferred_return_shape);
1393 TF_RET_CHECK(
1394 primitive_util::IsIntegralType(start_indices->shape().element_type()));
1395 TF_RET_CHECK(ShapeUtil::Compatible(result_shape, operand->shape()));
1396
1397 const Literal& operand_literal = parent_->GetEvaluatedLiteralFor(operand);
1398 const Literal& update_literal = parent_->GetEvaluatedLiteralFor(update);
1399 const Literal& start_indices_literal =
1400 parent_->GetEvaluatedLiteralFor(start_indices);
1401
1402 switch (start_indices->shape().element_type()) {
1403 case S32: {
1404 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(
1405 parent_->evaluated_[dynamic_update_slice],
1406 DynamicUpdateSlice<int32>(operand_literal, update_literal,
1407 start_indices_literal));
1408 } break;
1409 case S64: {
1410 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(
1411 parent_->evaluated_[dynamic_update_slice],
1412 DynamicUpdateSlice<int64>(operand_literal, update_literal,
1413 start_indices_literal));
1414 } break;
1415 case U32: {
1416 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(
1417 parent_->evaluated_[dynamic_update_slice],
1418 DynamicUpdateSlice<uint32>(operand_literal, update_literal,
1419 start_indices_literal));
1420 } break;
1421 case U64: {
1422 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(
1423 parent_->evaluated_[dynamic_update_slice],
1424 DynamicUpdateSlice<uint64>(operand_literal, update_literal,
1425 start_indices_literal));
1426 } break;
1427 default:
1428 LOG(FATAL) << "HandleDynamicUpdateSlice: unhandled primitive type for "
1429 "start_indices: "
1430 << PrimitiveType_Name(start_indices->shape().element_type());
1431 }
1432
1433 return Status::OK();
1434 }
1435
1436 template <typename NativeT>
1437 StatusOr<std::unique_ptr<Literal>> MapImpl(HloInstruction* map) {
1438 auto operands = map->operands();
1439 HloComputation* computation = map->to_apply();
1440
1441 auto result = Literal::CreateFromShape(map->shape());
1442
1443 HloEvaluator embedded_evaluator(parent_->max_loop_iterations_);
1444 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
1445 result->Populate<ReturnT>([&](ArraySlice<int64> multi_index) {
1446 std::vector<std::unique_ptr<Literal>> arg_literals;
1447 arg_literals.reserve(operands.size());
1448
1449 // Construct scalar literal parameters to be passed to the map
1450 // computation.
1451 for (auto operand : operands) {
1452 const Literal& arg_literal =
1453 parent_->GetEvaluatedLiteralFor(operand);
1454
1455 auto curr_val = arg_literal.Get<NativeT>(multi_index);
1456 auto curr_val_literal = Literal::CreateR0<NativeT>(curr_val);
1457
1458 arg_literals.push_back(std::move(curr_val_literal));
1459 }
1460
1461 std::unique_ptr<Literal> computed_result =
1462 embedded_evaluator
1463 .Evaluate<std::unique_ptr<Literal>>(*computation,
1464 arg_literals)
1465 .ConsumeValueOrDie();
1466 // Clear visit states so that the we can use the evaluate again on
1467 // the same computation.
1468 embedded_evaluator.ResetVisitStates();
1469
1470 return computed_result->Get<ReturnT>({});
1471 }));
1472 return std::move(result);
1473 }
1474
1475 Status HandleMap(HloInstruction* map) override {
1476 switch (map->operand(0)->shape().element_type()) {
1477 case PRED: {
1478 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(parent_->evaluated_[map], MapImpl<bool>(map));
1479 break;
1480 }
1481 case U8: {
1482 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(parent_->evaluated_[map], MapImpl<uint8>(map));
1483 break;
1484 }
1485 case U32: {
1486 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(parent_->evaluated_[map], MapImpl<uint32>(map));
1487 break;
1488 }
1489 case U64: {
1490 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(parent_->evaluated_[map], MapImpl<uint64>(map));
1491 break;
1492 }
1493 case S8: {
1494 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(parent_->evaluated_[map], MapImpl<int8>(map));
1495 break;
1496 }
1497 case S32: {
1498 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(parent_->evaluated_[map], MapImpl<int32>(map));
1499 break;
1500 }
1501 case S64: {
1502 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(parent_->evaluated_[map], MapImpl<int64>(map));
1503 break;
1504 }
1505 case F16: {
1506 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(parent_->evaluated_[map],
1507 MapImpl<Eigen::half>(map));
1508 break;
1509 }
1510 case F32: {
1511 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(parent_->evaluated_[map], MapImpl<float>(map));
1512 break;
1513 }
1514 case F64: {
1515 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(parent_->evaluated_[map], MapImpl<double>(map));
1516 break;
1517 }
1518 case C64: {
1519 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(parent_->evaluated_[map], MapImpl<complex64>(map));
1520 break;
1521 }
1522 default:
1523 LOG(FATAL) << "HandleMap: unhandled primitive type for "
1524 "input operand: "
1525 << PrimitiveType_Name(
1526 map->operand(0)->shape().element_type());
1527 }
1528
1529 return Status::OK();
1530 }
1531
1532 Status HandleReduce(HloInstruction* reduce) override {
1533 auto arg = reduce->operand(0);
1534 auto init_value = reduce->operand(1);
1535 ArraySlice<int64> dimensions(reduce->dimensions());
1536 HloComputation* function = reduce->to_apply();
1537 TF_RET_CHECK(ShapeUtil::Rank(reduce->shape()) ==
1538 ShapeUtil::Rank(arg->shape()) - dimensions.size());
1539 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(auto inferred_return_shape,
1540 ShapeInference::InferReduceShape(
1541 /*arg=*/arg->shape(),
1542 /*init_value=*/init_value->shape(),
1543 /*dimensions_to_reduce=*/dimensions,
1544 /*to_apply=*/function->ComputeProgramShape()));
1545 TF_RET_CHECK(ShapeUtil::Compatible(reduce->shape(), inferred_return_shape))
1546 << "return shape is set to: " << ShapeUtil::HumanString(reduce->shape())
1547 << "but is inferred to be: "
1548 << ShapeUtil::HumanString(inferred_return_shape);
1549
1550 const Literal& arg_literal = parent_->GetEvaluatedLiteralFor(arg);
1551 VLOG(3) << "HandleReduce arg_literal: " << arg_literal.ToString();
1552 const Literal& init_literal = parent_->GetEvaluatedLiteralFor(init_value);
1553 VLOG(3) << "HandleReduce init_literal: " << init_literal.ToString();
1554 TF_RET_CHECK(ShapeUtil::IsScalar(init_literal.shape()));
1555 auto init_scalar = init_literal.Get<ReturnT>({});
1556
1557 auto result = Literal::CreateFromShape(reduce->shape());
1558
1559 const auto arg_dimensions = AsInt64Slice(arg_literal.shape().dimensions());
1560 std::vector<int64> arg_dim_steps(arg_dimensions.size());
1561 std::vector<int64> arg_dim_counts(arg_dimensions.size());
1562 for (const int64 dim : dimensions) {
1563 arg_dim_steps[dim] = 1;
1564 arg_dim_counts[dim] = arg_dimensions[dim];
1565 }
1566
1567 // Map each dimension in the result to a dimension in arg that isn't
1568 // being reduced.
1569 std::vector<int64> result_to_arg_index;
1570 for (int64 i = 0; i < arg_dimensions.size(); ++i) {
1571 if (arg_dim_steps[i] == 0) {
1572 result_to_arg_index.push_back(i);
1573 }
1574 }
1575
1576 HloEvaluator embedded_evaluator(parent_->max_loop_iterations_);
1577 // For each resulting dimension, calculate and assign computed value.
1578 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
1579 result->Populate<ReturnT>([&](ArraySlice<int64> multi_index) {
1580 ReturnT result_val = init_scalar;
1581
1582 std::vector<int64> base(arg_dimensions.size());
1583 for (int64 i = 0; i < multi_index.size(); ++i) {
1584 base[result_to_arg_index[i]] = multi_index[i];
1585 }
1586
1587 // When the reduction is addition of floats, accumulate in a double
1588 // for better precision. Also, avoid creating Literals for the
1589 // intermediate results; it's much faster.
1590 if (ShapeUtil::ElementIsFloating(init_literal.shape()) &&
1591 IsScalarAdd(function)) {
1592 double computed_result = 0;
1593 auto func = [&](ArraySlice<int64> input_index) {
1594 computed_result += arg_literal.Get<float>(input_index);
1595 return true;
1596 };
1597 ShapeUtil::ForEachIndex(arg_literal.shape(), base, arg_dim_counts,
1598 arg_dim_steps, func);
1599 return static_cast<ReturnT>(computed_result);
1600 }
1601 auto func = [&](ArraySlice<int64> input_index) {
1602 auto curr_val = arg_literal.Get<ReturnT>(input_index);
1603
1604 // Evaluate computation with specified literal operands.
1605 auto curr_val_literal = Literal::CreateR0<ReturnT>(curr_val);
1606 auto result_val_literal = Literal::CreateR0<ReturnT>(result_val);
1607 std::vector<const Literal*> args = {curr_val_literal.get(),
1608 result_val_literal.get()};
1609
1610 std::unique_ptr<Literal> computed_result =
1611 embedded_evaluator.Evaluate<const Literal*>(*function, args)
1612 .ConsumeValueOrDie();
1613 // Clear visit states so that we can use the evaluator again on
1614 // the same computation.
1615 embedded_evaluator.ResetVisitStates();
1616 // Assign computed result to result_val.
1617 result_val = computed_result->Get<ReturnT>({});
1618 return true;
1619 };
1620 // Computes one element of the result, reducing all dimensions that
1621 // contribute to that element.
1622 ShapeUtil::ForEachIndex(arg_literal.shape(), base, arg_dim_counts,
1623 arg_dim_steps, func);
1624 return result_val;
1625 }));
1626
1627 parent_->evaluated_[reduce] = std::move(result);
1628 return Status::OK();
1629 }
1630
1631 bool IsScalarAdd(HloComputation* computation) {
1632 HloInstruction* instruction = computation->root_instruction();
1633 if (instruction->opcode() == HloOpcode::kAdd &&
1634 computation->num_parameters() == 2) {
1635 const HloInstruction* lhs = instruction->operand(0);
1636 const HloInstruction* rhs = instruction->operand(1);
1637 return lhs->opcode() == HloOpcode::kParameter &&
1638 ShapeUtil::IsScalar(lhs->shape()) &&
1639 rhs->opcode() == HloOpcode::kParameter &&
1640 ShapeUtil::IsScalar(rhs->shape()) && lhs != rhs;
1641 }
1642 return false;
1643 }
1644
1645 Status HandleSelectAndScatter(HloInstruction* select_and_scatter) override {
1646 auto operand = select_and_scatter->operand(0);
1647 auto source = select_and_scatter->operand(1);
1648 const Window& window = select_and_scatter->window();
1649
1650 const Literal& init_literal =
1651 parent_->GetEvaluatedLiteralFor(select_and_scatter->operand(2));
1652 TF_RET_CHECK(ShapeUtil::IsScalar(init_literal.shape()));
1653 auto init_scalar = init_literal.Get<ReturnT>({});
1654
1655 auto result = Literal::CreateFromShape(select_and_scatter->shape());
1656
1657 // Initialize result array with the init value.
1658 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(result->Populate<ReturnT>(
1659 [&](ArraySlice<int64> output_index) { return init_scalar; }));
1660
1661 std::vector<int64> window_dimension_sizes;
1662 for (const auto& window_dimension : window.dimensions()) {
1663 window_dimension_sizes.push_back(window_dimension.size());
1664 }
1665 const Shape window_shape = ShapeUtil::MakeShape(
1666 operand->shape().element_type(), window_dimension_sizes);
1667
1668 HloComputation* select = select_and_scatter->select();
1669 HloComputation* scatter = select_and_scatter->scatter();
1670
1671 const Literal& operand_literal = parent_->GetEvaluatedLiteralFor(operand);
1672 const Literal& source_literal = parent_->GetEvaluatedLiteralFor(source);
1673
1674 int64 rank = ShapeUtil::Rank(operand_literal.shape());
1675
1676 HloEvaluator embedded_evaluator(parent_->max_loop_iterations_);
1677 DimensionVector source_index(rank);
1678
1679 std::fill(source_index.begin(), source_index.end(), 0);
1680 do {
1681 // For each element in `source`, we place a window in `operand`. For each
1682 // window placement, we iterate inside the window twice:
1683 //
1684 // 1. Find the selected index by applying `select` function to all
1685 // elements. E.g., If the `select` function is GreaterEqual, the first
1686 // iteration through the window finds the biggest value and returns its
1687 // index.
1688 //
1689 // 2. Using the selected index, scatter value from `source` to result. We
1690 // do this by iterating through the window, and compare each index with
1691 // the selected index.
1692 optional<ReturnT> selected_val;
1693 optional<std::vector<int64>> selected_index;
1694
1695 IterateThroughWindow(
1696 window_shape, window, operand_literal.shape(), source_index,
1697 [&](const std::vector<int64>& operand_index) {
1698 auto curr_val = operand_literal.Get<ReturnT>(operand_index);
1699 if (!selected_val) {
1700 selected_val = curr_val;
1701 selected_index = operand_index;
1702 }
1703 const auto curr_val_literal = Literal::CreateR0<ReturnT>(curr_val);
1704 const auto selected_val_literal =
1705 Literal::CreateR0<ReturnT>(*selected_val);
1706
1707 const std::vector<const Literal*> args = {
1708 selected_val_literal.get(), curr_val_literal.get()};
1709 std::unique_ptr<Literal> computed_result =
1710 embedded_evaluator.Evaluate<const Literal*>(*select, args)
1711 .ConsumeValueOrDie();
1712 bool selected = !computed_result->Get<bool>({});
1713 if (selected) {
1714 selected_val = curr_val;
1715 selected_index = operand_index;
1716 }
1717 embedded_evaluator.ResetVisitStates();
1718 });
1719
1720 IterateThroughWindow(
1721 window_shape, window, operand_literal.shape(), source_index,
1722 [&](const std::vector<int64>& operand_index) {
1723 if (std::equal(operand_index.begin(), operand_index.end(),
1724 selected_index->begin())) {
1725 auto source = source_literal.Get<ReturnT>(source_index);
1726 auto scattered = result->Get<ReturnT>(operand_index);
1727 const auto source_literal = Literal::CreateR0<ReturnT>(source);
1728 const auto scattered_literal =
1729 Literal::CreateR0<ReturnT>(scattered);
1730
1731 const std::vector<const Literal*> args = {
1732 source_literal.get(), scattered_literal.get()};
1733 std::unique_ptr<Literal> computed_result =
1734 embedded_evaluator.Evaluate<const Literal*>(*scatter, args)
1735 .ConsumeValueOrDie();
1736 result->Set(operand_index, computed_result->Get<ReturnT>({}));
1737 // Clear visit states so that the we can use the evaluator again
1738 // on the same computation.
1739 embedded_evaluator.ResetVisitStates();
1740 }
1741 });
1742 } while (IndexUtil::BumpIndices(source->shape(), &source_index));
1743
1744 parent_->evaluated_[select_and_scatter] = std::move(result);
1745 return Status::OK();
1746 }
1747
1748 Status HandleReduceWindow(HloInstruction* reduce_window) override {
1749 auto operand = reduce_window->operand(0);
1750 const Window& window = reduce_window->window();
1751 HloComputation* function = reduce_window->to_apply();
1752 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(
1753 auto inferred_return_shape,
1754 ShapeInference::InferReduceWindowShape(
1755 /*operand_shape=*/reduce_window->operand(0)->shape(),
1756 /*init_value=*/reduce_window->operand(1)->shape(), window,
1757 /*to_apply_shape=*/function->ComputeProgramShape()));
1758 TF_RET_CHECK(
1759 ShapeUtil::Compatible(reduce_window->shape(), inferred_return_shape))
1760 << "return shape is set to: "
1761 << ShapeUtil::HumanStringWithLayout(reduce_window->shape())
1762 << "but is inferred to be: "
1763 << ShapeUtil::HumanStringWithLayout(inferred_return_shape);
1764
1765 const Literal& operand_literal =
1766 parent_->GetEvaluatedLiteralFor(reduce_window->operand(0));
1767 VLOG(3) << "HandleReduceWindow arg_literal: " << operand_literal.ToString();
1768 const Literal& init_literal =
1769 parent_->GetEvaluatedLiteralFor(reduce_window->operand(1));
1770 VLOG(3) << "HandleReduceWindow init_literal: " << init_literal.ToString();
1771 TF_RET_CHECK(ShapeUtil::IsScalar(init_literal.shape()));
1772 auto init_scalar = init_literal.Get<ReturnT>({});
1773
1774 auto result = Literal::CreateFromShape(reduce_window->shape());
1775
1776 // Creates a Shape object from window, for iteration below.
1777 std::vector<int64> window_dimension_sizes;
1778 for (const auto& window_dimension : window.dimensions()) {
1779 window_dimension_sizes.push_back(window_dimension.size());
1780 }
1781 const Shape window_shape = ShapeUtil::MakeShape(
1782 operand->shape().element_type(), window_dimension_sizes);
1783
1784 DimensionVector window_index(window.dimensions_size());
1785 DimensionVector operand_index(ShapeUtil::Rank(operand_literal.shape()));
1786
1787 HloEvaluator embedded_evaluator(parent_->max_loop_iterations_);
1788 // For each resulting dimension, calculate and assign computed value.
1789 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
1790 result->Populate<ReturnT>([&](ArraySlice<int64> output_index) {
1791 ReturnT result_val = init_scalar;
1792
1793 std::fill(window_index.begin(), window_index.end(), 0);
1794 std::fill(operand_index.begin(), operand_index.end(), 0);
1795
1796 IterateThroughWindow(
1797 window_shape, window, operand_literal.shape(), output_index,
1798 [&](const std::vector<int64>& operand_index) {
1799 auto curr_val = operand_literal.Get<ReturnT>(operand_index);
1800
1801 // Evaluate computation with specified literal operands.
1802 const auto curr_val_literal =
1803 Literal::CreateR0<ReturnT>(curr_val);
1804 const auto result_val_literal =
1805 Literal::CreateR0<ReturnT>(result_val);
1806 const std::vector<const Literal*> args = {
1807 curr_val_literal.get(), result_val_literal.get()};
1808 std::unique_ptr<Literal> computed_result =
1809 embedded_evaluator.Evaluate<const Literal*>(*function, args)
1810 .ConsumeValueOrDie();
1811
1812 // Clear visit states so that the we can use the evaluate again
1813 // on the same computation.
1814 embedded_evaluator.ResetVisitStates();
1815
1816 result_val = computed_result->Get<ReturnT>({});
1817 });
1818
1819 return result_val;
1820 }));
1821
1822 parent_->evaluated_[reduce_window] = std::move(result);
1823 return Status::OK();
1824 }
1825
1826 Status HandleSlice(HloInstruction* slice) override {
1827 auto operand = slice->operand(0);
1828 const Shape& shape = slice->shape();
1829 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(auto inferred_return_shape,
1830 ShapeInference::InferSliceShape(
1831 operand->shape(), slice->slice_starts(),
1832 slice->slice_limits(), slice->slice_strides()));
1833 TF_RET_CHECK(ShapeUtil::Compatible(shape, inferred_return_shape))
1834 << "return shape set to: " << ShapeUtil::HumanString(shape)
1835 << " but is inferred to be: "
1836 << ShapeUtil::HumanString(inferred_return_shape);
1837
1838 const int64 rank = ShapeUtil::Rank(operand->shape());
1839 const Literal& operand_literal = parent_->GetEvaluatedLiteralFor(operand);
1840 auto func = [&](ArraySlice<int64> out_index) {
1841 DimensionVector operand_index(rank);
1842 for (int64 i = 0; i < rank; ++i) {
1843 operand_index[i] =
1844 slice->slice_starts(i) + out_index[i] * slice->slice_strides(i);
1845 }
1846 return operand_literal.Get<ReturnT>(operand_index);
1847 };
1848
1849 auto result = Literal::CreateFromDimensions(
1850 shape.element_type(), AsInt64Slice(shape.dimensions()));
1851 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(result->Populate<ReturnT>(func));
1852 parent_->evaluated_[slice] = std::move(result);
1853 return Status::OK();
1854 }

1900 template <typename NativeT, typename std::enable_if<std::is_same<
1901 float, NativeT>::value>::type* = nullptr>
1902 Status HandleReducePrecision(HloInstruction* reduce_precision) {
1903 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(
1904 parent_->evaluated_[reduce_precision],
1905 ElementWiseUnaryOp(reduce_precision, [reduce_precision](
1906 ElementwiseT elem) {
1907 uint32_t value_as_int = tensorflow::bit_cast<uint32_t>(elem);
1908 const uint32_t mantissa_bits = reduce_precision->mantissa_bits();
1909 const uint32_t exponent_bits = reduce_precision->exponent_bits();
1910
1911 // Code is based on the CPU/GPU implementation in LLVM-emitting code.
1912 //
1913 // Bits in float type:
1914 // mantissa : bits [0:22]
1915 // exponent : bits [23:30]
1916 // sign : bits [31]
1917 if (mantissa_bits < 23) {
1918 const uint32_t last_mantissa_bit_mask = 1u << (23 - mantissa_bits);
1919
1920 // Compute rounding bias for round-to-nearest with ties to even.
1921 // This is equal to a base value of 0111... plus one bit if the last
1922 // remaining mantissa bit is 1.
1923 const uint32_t base_rounding_bias =
1924 (last_mantissa_bit_mask >> 1) - 1;
1925 const uint32_t x_last_mantissa_bit =
1926 (value_as_int & last_mantissa_bit_mask) >> (23 - mantissa_bits);
1927 const uint32_t x_rounding_bias =
1928 x_last_mantissa_bit + base_rounding_bias;
1929
1930 // Add rounding bias, and mask out truncated bits. Note that the
1931 // case where adding the rounding bias overflows into the exponent
1932 // bits is correct; the non-masked mantissa bits will all be zero,
1933 // and the exponent will be incremented by one.
1934 const uint32_t truncation_mask = ~(last_mantissa_bit_mask - 1);
1935 value_as_int = value_as_int + x_rounding_bias;
1936 value_as_int = value_as_int & truncation_mask;
1937 }
1938 if (exponent_bits < 8) {
1939 // Masks for f32 values.
1940 const uint32_t f32_sign_bit_mask = 1u << 31;
1941 const uint32_t f32_exp_bits_mask = 0xffu << 23;
1942
1943 // An exponent of 2^(n-1)-1 -- that is, 0111... with the zero in the
1944 // most- significant bit -- is equal to 1.0f for all exponent sizes.
1945 // Adding 2^(n-1)-1 to this gives us the highest non-infinite
1946 // exponent for a bit- size of n, and subtracting 2^(n-1)-1 from
1947 // this gives us the lowest' exponent (corresponding to 0.0f).
1948 //
1949 // Thus, the f32 exponent corresponding to the highest non-infinite
1950 // exponent for a bit size of n is (2^7-1) + 2^(n-1)-1, and the f32
1951 // exponent corresponding to the lowest exponent for a bit size of n
1952 // is (2^7-1) - 2^(n-1)-1.
1953 //
1954 // Note that we have already checked that exponents_bits >= 1.
1955 const uint32_t f32_exponent_bias = (1 << 7) - 1;
1956 const uint32_t reduced_exponent_bias =
1957 (1 << (exponent_bits - 1)) - 1;
1958 const uint32_t reduced_max_exponent =
1959 f32_exponent_bias + reduced_exponent_bias;
1960 const uint32_t reduced_min_exponent =
1961 f32_exponent_bias - reduced_exponent_bias;
1962
1963 // Do we overflow or underflow?
1964 const uint32_t x_exponent = value_as_int & f32_exp_bits_mask;
1965 const bool x_overflows = x_exponent > (reduced_max_exponent << 23);
1966 const bool x_underflows =
1967 x_exponent <= (reduced_min_exponent << 23);
1968
1969 // Compute appropriately-signed values of zero and infinity.
1970 const uint32_t x_signed_zero = value_as_int & f32_sign_bit_mask;
1971 const uint32_t x_signed_inf = x_signed_zero | f32_exp_bits_mask;
1972
1973 // Force to zero or infinity if overflow or underflow. (Note that
1974 // this truncates all denormal values to zero, rather than rounding
1975 // them.)
1976 value_as_int = x_overflows ? x_signed_inf : value_as_int;
1977 value_as_int = x_underflows ? x_signed_zero : value_as_int;
1978 }
1979
1980 float reduced_result = tensorflow::bit_cast<float>(value_as_int);
1981 if (std::isnan(elem)) {
1982 reduced_result = mantissa_bits > 0
1983 ? elem
1984 : std::numeric_limits<float>::infinity();
1985 }
1986 return reduced_result;
1987 }));
1988 return Status::OK();
1989 }

1991 template <typename NativeT, typename std::enable_if<std::is_same<
1992 double, NativeT>::value>::type* = nullptr>
1993 Status HandleReducePrecision(HloInstruction* reduce_precision) {
1994 return InvalidArgument("Double not supported for reduce precision");
1995 }

2002 return InvalidArgument("Unsupported type for reduce precision");

2009 private:
2010 template <typename IndexT>
2011 StatusOr<std::unique_ptr<Literal>> DynamicSlice(
2012 const Literal& operand_literal, const Literal& start_indices_literal,
2013 const Shape& result_shape) {
2014 auto start_indices_typed = start_indices_literal.data<IndexT>();
2015 std::vector<int64> start(start_indices_typed.begin(),
2016 start_indices_typed.end());
2017
2018 std::vector<int64> operand_indices(start.size());
2019
2020 auto result = Literal::CreateFromShape(result_shape);
2021 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
2022 result->Populate<ReturnT>([&](ArraySlice<int64> multi_index) {
2023 for (int64 i = 0; i < operand_indices.size(); ++i) {
2024 CHECK_GE(multi_index[i] + start[i], 0);
2025 // Mod is only used here to be consistent with the existing
2026 // backends' behavior.
2027 operand_indices[i] = (multi_index[i] + start[i]) %
2028 operand_literal.shape().dimensions(i);
2029 }
2030
2031 auto result = operand_literal.Get<ReturnT>(operand_indices);
2032 return result;
2033 }));
2034
2035 return std::move(result);
2036 }
2037
2038 template <typename IndexT>
2039 StatusOr<std::unique_ptr<Literal>> DynamicUpdateSlice(
2040 const Literal& operand_literal, const Literal& update_literal,
2041 const Literal& start_indices_literal) {
2042 auto result = operand_literal.CloneToUnique();
2043 auto start_indices_typed = start_indices_literal.data<IndexT>();
2044 const auto rank = ShapeUtil::Rank(result->shape());
2045 std::vector<int64> start(rank, 0);
2046 for (int64 i = 0; i < rank; ++i) {
2047 // All other implementations currently wrap-around the index, so this
2048 // should do so as well.
2049 start[i] = (start_indices_typed[i] % result->shape().dimensions(i));
2050 start[i] += (start[i] < 0) * result->shape().dimensions(i);
2051 }
2052 std::vector<int64> result_index(rank, 0);
2053
2054 auto func = [&](ArraySlice<int64> update_index) {
2055 std::transform(update_index.begin(), update_index.end(), start.begin(),
2056 result_index.begin(), std::plus<int64>());
2057 // Same as above, wrap-around only to match other implementations'
2058 // semantics.
2059 std::transform(result_index.begin(), result_index.end(),
2060 result->shape().dimensions().begin(), result_index.begin(),
2061 std::modulus<int64>());
2062 result->Set<ReturnT>(result_index,
2063 update_literal.Get<ReturnT>(update_index));
2064 return true;
2065 };
2066
2067 std::vector<int64> base(update_literal.shape().dimensions_size(), 0);
2068 std::vector<int64> step(update_literal.shape().dimensions_size(), 1);
2069 ShapeUtil::ForEachIndex(update_literal.shape(), base,
2070 AsInt64Slice(update_literal.shape().dimensions()),
2071 step, func);
2072
2073 return std::move(result);
2074 }

2080 parent_->GetEvaluatedLiteralFor(instruction->operand(0));
2081 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(
2082 auto result_literal,

2085

2088
2089 StatusOr<std::unique_ptr<Literal>> ElementWiseBinaryOp(
2090 HloInstruction* instruction,
2091 const std::function<ElementwiseT(ElementwiseT, ElementwiseT)>&
2092 binary_op) {
2093 const auto shape = instruction->shape();
2094 const auto* lhs = instruction->operand(0);
2095 const auto* rhs = instruction->operand(1);
2096
2097 // TODO(b/35950897, b/27796129): add DCHECK back once implicit broadcast
2098 // is removed.
2099 if (!(ShapeUtil::SameDimensions(shape, rhs->shape()) &&
2100 ShapeUtil::SameDimensions(lhs->shape(), rhs->shape()))) {
2101 return Unimplemented(
2102 "Implicit broadcasting is currently unsupported in HLO evaluator "
2103 "Shape Mismatch: %s vs %s vs %s: ",
2104 ShapeUtil::HumanString(shape).c_str(),
2105 ShapeUtil::HumanString(lhs->shape()).c_str(),
2106 ShapeUtil::HumanString(rhs->shape()).c_str());
2107 }
2108
2109 const Literal& lhs_literal = parent_->GetEvaluatedLiteralFor(lhs);
2110 const Literal& rhs_literal = parent_->GetEvaluatedLiteralFor(rhs);
2111
2112 auto result = Literal::CreateFromShape(shape);
2113
2114 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
2115 result->Populate<ReturnT>([&](ArraySlice<int64> multi_index) {
2116 return ConvertBinaryFunction(binary_op)(
2117 lhs_literal.Get<ReturnT>(multi_index),
2118 rhs_literal.Get<ReturnT>(multi_index));
2119 }));
2120 return std::move(result);
2121 }

2123 template <typename LhsType, typename RhsType, typename EhsType>
2124 StatusOr<std::unique_ptr<Literal>> ElementwiseTernaryOp(
2125 HloInstruction* instruction,
2126 const std::function<ReturnT(LhsType, RhsType, EhsType)>& ternary_op) {
2127 const auto shape = instruction->shape();
2128 const auto* lhs = instruction->operand(0);
2129 const auto* rhs = instruction->operand(1);
2130 const auto* ehs = instruction->operand(2);
2131
2132 // TODO(b/35950897, b/27796129): add DCHECK back once implicit
2133 // broadcast is removed.
2134 if (!(ShapeUtil::SameDimensions(shape, lhs->shape()) &&
2135 ShapeUtil::SameDimensions(lhs->shape(), rhs->shape()) &&
2136 ShapeUtil::SameDimensions(rhs->shape(), ehs->shape()))) {
2137 return Unimplemented(
2138 "Implicit broadcasting is currently unsupported in HLO evaluator "
2139 "Shape Mismatch: %s vs %s vs %s vs %s: ",
2140 ShapeUtil::HumanString(shape).c_str(),
2141 ShapeUtil::HumanString(lhs->shape()).c_str(),
2142 ShapeUtil::HumanString(rhs->shape()).c_str(),
2143 ShapeUtil::HumanString(ehs->shape()).c_str());
2144 }
2145
2146 const Literal& lhs_literal = parent_->GetEvaluatedLiteralFor(lhs);
2147 const Literal& rhs_literal = parent_->GetEvaluatedLiteralFor(rhs);
2148 const Literal& ehs_literal = parent_->GetEvaluatedLiteralFor(ehs);
2149
2150 auto result = Literal::CreateFromShape(shape);
2151
2152 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
2153 result->Populate<ReturnT>([&](ArraySlice<int64> multi_index) {
2154 return ternary_op(lhs_literal.Get<LhsType>(multi_index),
2155 rhs_literal.Get<RhsType>(multi_index),
2156 ehs_literal.Get<EhsType>(multi_index));
2157 }));
2158
2159 return std::move(result);
2160 }

2162 template <typename NativeT>
2163 static bool IsShiftOutOfBounds(NativeT rhs) {
2164 typedef typename std::make_unsigned<NativeT>::type UnsignedT;
2165 UnsignedT lhs_size_unsigned = sizeof(NativeT) * CHAR_BIT;
2166 UnsignedT rhs_unsigned = static_cast<UnsignedT>(rhs);
2167 return rhs_unsigned >= lhs_size_unsigned;
2168 }

2173HloEvaluator::HloEvaluator(int64 max_loop_iterations)
2174 : max_loop_iterations_(max_loop_iterations) {
2175 typed_visitors_[PRED] = MakeUnique<TypedVisitor<bool>>(this);
2176 typed_visitors_[U8] = MakeUnique<TypedVisitor<uint8>>(this);
2177 typed_visitors_[U16] = MakeUnique<FunctionVisitor>([](HloInstruction*) {
2178 return Unimplemented(
2179 "HloEvaluator::TypedVisitor: unhandled primitive type: U16.");
2180 });
2181 typed_visitors_[U32] = MakeUnique<TypedVisitor<uint32>>(this);
2182 typed_visitors_[U64] = MakeUnique<TypedVisitor<uint64>>(this);
2183 typed_visitors_[S8] = MakeUnique<TypedVisitor<int8>>(this);
2184 typed_visitors_[S16] = MakeUnique<FunctionVisitor>([](HloInstruction*) {
2185 return Unimplemented(
2186 "HloEvaluator::TypedVisitor: unhandled primitive type: S16.");
2187 });
2188 typed_visitors_[S32] = MakeUnique<TypedVisitor<int32>>(this);
2189 typed_visitors_[S64] = MakeUnique<TypedVisitor<int64>>(this);
2190 typed_visitors_[F16] = MakeUnique<TypedVisitor<Eigen::half, float>>(this);
2191 typed_visitors_[F32] = MakeUnique<TypedVisitor<float>>(this);
2192 typed_visitors_[F64] = MakeUnique<TypedVisitor<double>>(this);
2193 typed_visitors_[C64] = MakeUnique<TypedVisitor<complex64>>(this);
2194
2195 // Most of the evaluator computations we use don't support BF16 (e.g.,
2196 // std::ceil, std::tanh). To make evaluator work with BF16, we set all
2197 // elementwise computations to be done in F32 and do BF16<->F32 conversion
2198 // around the input and the output of the computations.
2199 typed_visitors_[BF16] = MakeUnique<TypedVisitor<bfloat16, float>>(this);
2200
2201 typed_visitors_[TUPLE] = MakeUnique<FunctionVisitor>([](HloInstruction*) {
2202 return Unimplemented(
2203 "HloEvaluator::TypedVistor: unhandled primitive type: TUPLE.");
2204 });
2205 typed_visitors_[OPAQUE] = MakeUnique<FunctionVisitor>([](HloInstruction*) {
2206 return Unimplemented(
2207 "HloEvaluator::TypedVisitor: unhandled primitive type: OPAQUE.");
2208 });
2209}

2232 XLA_VLOG_LINES(
2233 2, "HloEvaluator::Evaluate computation:\n" + computation.ToString());
2234
2235 evaluated_.clear();
2236 arg_literals_.clear();
2237 for (const auto& literal_ptr : arg_literals) {
2238 arg_literals_.push_back(&*literal_ptr);
2239 }
2240

2245template <typename LiteralPtr>
2246StatusOr<std::unique_ptr<Literal>> HloEvaluator::Evaluate(
2247 HloInstruction* instruction, ArraySlice<LiteralPtr> arg_literals) {
2248 TF_RET_CHECK(hlo_query::AllOperandsAreParametersOrConstants(*instruction));
2249 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(ShapeUtil::ValidateShape(instruction->shape()));
2250
2251 evaluated_.clear();
2252 arg_literals_.clear();
2253 for (const auto& literal_ptr : arg_literals) {
2254 arg_literals_.push_back(&*literal_ptr);
2255 }
2256
2257 // Evaluate operands of Parameter type against the input literals which
2258 // caches the evaluated literal results.
2259 for (const auto operand : instruction->operands()) {
2260 if (operand->opcode() == HloOpcode::kParameter) {
2261 const Literal* input_literal = arg_literals_[operand->parameter_number()];
2262 VLOG(2) << "Parameter operand evaluated to: "
2263 << input_literal->ToString();
2264 TF_RET_CHECK(ShapeUtil::Equal(operand->shape(), input_literal->shape()));
2265
2266 evaluated_[operand] = input_literal->CloneToUnique();
2267 }
2268 }
2269
2270 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(Preprocess(instruction));
2271 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(instruction->Visit(this));
2272 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(Postprocess(instruction));
2273 return GetEvaluatedLiteralFor(instruction).CloneToUnique();
2274}
2275
2276StatusOr<std::unique_ptr<Literal>> HloEvaluator::Evaluate(
2277 HloInstruction* instruction) {
2278 if (instruction->opcode() == HloOpcode::kParameter) {
2279 return tensorflow::errors::FailedPrecondition(
2280 "Cannot evaluate a parameter.");
2281 }
2282 if (!hlo_query::AllOperandsAreConstants(*instruction)) {
2283 return tensorflow::errors::FailedPrecondition(
2284 "Not all operands are constants.");
2285 }
2286 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(ShapeUtil::ValidateShape(instruction->shape()));
2287
2288 arg_literals_.clear();
2289 evaluated_.clear();
2290
2291 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(Preprocess(instruction));
2292 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(instruction->Visit(this));
2293 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(Postprocess(instruction));
2294 return GetEvaluatedLiteralFor(instruction).CloneToUnique();
2295}

2297std::unique_ptr<Literal> HloEvaluator::TryEvaluate(
2298 HloInstruction* instruction) {
2299 auto result_or = Evaluate(instruction);
2300 if (!result_or.ok()) {
2301 VLOG(1) << "TryEvaluate failed:" << result_or.status();
2302 return nullptr;
2303 }
2304
2305 return result_or.ConsumeValueOrDie();
2306}
2307
2308StatusOr<std::unique_ptr<Literal>> HloEvaluator::EvaluateWithSubstitutions(
2309 const HloInstruction* instruction,
2310 const std::unordered_map<const HloInstruction*, const Literal*>&
2311 substitutions) {
2312 std::vector<std::unique_ptr<HloInstruction>> owned_operands;
2313 for (const HloInstruction* operand : instruction->operands()) {
2314 auto it = substitutions.find(operand);
2315 if (it == substitutions.end()) {
2316 owned_operands.push_back(operand->Clone());
2317 } else {
2318 owned_operands.push_back(
2319 HloInstruction::CreateConstant(it->second->CloneToUnique()));
2320 }
2321 }
2322
2323 std::vector<HloInstruction*> operands;
2324 operands.reserve(owned_operands.size());
2325 for (auto& operand : owned_operands) {
2326 operands.push_back(operand.get());
2327 }
2328
2329 std::unique_ptr<HloInstruction> cloned_instruction =
2330 instruction->CloneWithNewOperands(instruction->shape(), operands);
2331 auto result = Evaluate(cloned_instruction.get());
2332
2333 // Clean up our cloned instructions before returning.
2334 cloned_instruction->DetachFromOperands();
2335 for (auto& operand : owned_operands) {
2336 operand->DetachFromOperands();
2337 }
2338
2339 return result;
2340}

2342Status HloEvaluator::HandleParameter(HloInstruction* parameter) {
2343 CHECK_LT(parameter->parameter_number(), arg_literals_.size());
2344 const Literal* input_literal = arg_literals_[parameter->parameter_number()];
2345 VLOG(2) << "Parameter evaluated to: " << input_literal->ToString();
2346 DCHECK(ShapeUtil::Equal(parameter->shape(), input_literal->shape()))
2347 << "parameter shape is: " << ShapeUtil::HumanString(parameter->shape())
2348 << ", but input literal shape is: "
2349 << ShapeUtil::HumanString(input_literal->shape());
2350
2351 evaluated_[parameter] = input_literal->CloneToUnique();
2352 return Status::OK();
2353}
