2370
2371Status HloEvaluator::HandleConcatenate(HloInstruction* concatenate) {
2372 ArraySlice<HloInstruction*> operands(concatenate->operands());
2373 // The result concatenate dimension is going to be the sum of all
2374 // concatenate dimensions of the operands taking part of the operation.
2375 const Shape& reference_shape = operands[0]->shape();
2376 CHECK(!ShapeUtil::IsTuple(reference_shape));
2377 const int64 rank = ShapeUtil::Rank(reference_shape);
2378 const int64 concat_dim = concatenate->dimensions()[0];
2379 CHECK_GE(concat_dim, 0);
2380 CHECK_LT(concat_dim, rank);
2381
2382 DimensionVector concat_dimensions(reference_shape.dimensions().begin(),
2383 reference_shape.dimensions().end());
2384
2385 for (int64 i = 1; i < operands.size(); ++i) {
2386 const Shape& operand_shape = operands[i]->shape();
2387 CHECK(!ShapeUtil::IsTuple(operand_shape));
2388 // Accumulate the concat dimension from all tensors taking part to the
2389 // operation.
2390 concat_dimensions[concat_dim] +=
2391 ShapeUtil::GetDimension(operand_shape, concat_dim);
2392 }
2393
2394 auto result_literal = Literal::CreateFromDimensions(
2395 reference_shape.element_type(), concat_dimensions);
2396 DimensionVector source_indices(rank, 0);
2397 DimensionVector dest_indices(concat_dimensions.size(), 0);
2398
2399 for (auto operand : operands) {
2400 const Shape& operand_shape = operand->shape();
2401 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(result_literal->CopySliceFrom(
2402 GetEvaluatedLiteralFor(operand), source_indices, dest_indices,
2403 AsInt64Slice(operand_shape.dimensions())));
2404 dest_indices[concat_dim] +=
2405 ShapeUtil::GetDimension(operand_shape, concat_dim);
2406 }
2407
2408 evaluated_[concatenate] = std::move(result_literal);
2409 return Status::OK();
2410}
2411
2412Status HloEvaluator::HandleIsFinite(HloInstruction* is_finite) {
2413 auto operand = is_finite->operand(0);
2414 if (!ShapeUtil::ElementIsFloating(operand->shape())) {
2415 return InvalidArgument(
2416 "expected element type in shape to be float for IsFinite op, got: %s",
2417 PrimitiveType_Name(operand->shape().element_type()).c_str());
2418 }
2419
2420 switch (operand->shape().element_type()) {
2421 case F16:
2422 return Unimplemented("unhandled primitive type: F16.");
2423 case F32: {
2424 auto result_or = ElementWiseUnaryOpImpl<bool, float>(
2425 is_finite,
2426 [](float elem_operand) { return std::isfinite(elem_operand); },
2427 GetEvaluatedLiteralFor(operand));
2428 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(evaluated_[is_finite], std::move(result_or));
2429 break;
2430 }
2431 case F64: {
2432 auto result_or = ElementWiseUnaryOpImpl<bool, double>(
2433 is_finite,
2434 [](double elem_operand) { return std::isfinite(elem_operand); },
2435 GetEvaluatedLiteralFor(operand));
2436 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(evaluated_[is_finite], std::move(result_or));
2437 break;
2438 }
2439 default:
2440 LOG(FATAL) << "HandleIsFinite: unknown/unhandled primitive type: "
2441 << PrimitiveType_Name(operand->shape().element_type());
2442 }
2443
2444 return Status::OK();
2445}
2446
2447Status HloEvaluator::HandleCompare(HloInstruction* compare) {
2448 HloOpcode opcode = compare->opcode();
2449 auto lhs = compare->operand(0);
2450 auto rhs = compare->operand(1);
2451 // TODO(b/35950897, b/27796129): add DCHECK back once implicit broadcast is
2452 // removed.
2453 if (!(ShapeUtil::SameDimensions(compare->shape(), rhs->shape()) &&
2454 ShapeUtil::SameDimensions(lhs->shape(), rhs->shape()))) {
2455 return Unimplemented(
2456 "Implicit broadcasting is currently unsupported in HLO evaluator "
2457 "Shape Mismatch: %s vs %s vs %s",
2458 ShapeUtil::HumanString(compare->shape()).c_str(),
2459 ShapeUtil::HumanString(lhs->shape()).c_str(),
2460 ShapeUtil::HumanString(rhs->shape()).c_str());
2461 }
2462
2463 TF_RET_CHECK(lhs->shape().element_type() == rhs->shape().element_type());
2464
2465 const Literal& lhs_literal = GetEvaluatedLiteralFor(lhs);
2466 const Literal& rhs_literal = GetEvaluatedLiteralFor(rhs);
2467
2468 // Note here we switch on the operand's type.
2469 switch (lhs->shape().element_type()) {
2470 case PRED: {
2471 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(
2472 evaluated_[compare],
2473 Compare<bool>(compare->shape(), opcode, lhs_literal, rhs_literal));
2474 } break;
2475 case U8: {
2476 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(
2477 evaluated_[compare],
2478 Compare<uint8>(compare->shape(), opcode, lhs_literal, rhs_literal));
2479 } break;
2480 case U16:
2481 return Unimplemented("unhandled primitive type: U16.");
2482 case U32: {
2483 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(
2484 evaluated_[compare],
2485 Compare<uint32>(compare->shape(), opcode, lhs_literal, rhs_literal));
2486 } break;
2487 case U64: {
2488 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(
2489 evaluated_[compare],
2490 Compare<uint64>(compare->shape(), opcode, lhs_literal, rhs_literal));
2491 } break;
2492 case S8: {
2493 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(
2494 evaluated_[compare],
2495 Compare<int8>(compare->shape(), opcode, lhs_literal, rhs_literal));
2496 } break;
2497 case S16:
2498 return Unimplemented("unhandled primitive type: S16.");
2499 case S32: {
2500 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(
2501 evaluated_[compare],
2502 Compare<int32>(compare->shape(), opcode, lhs_literal, rhs_literal));
2503 } break;
2504 case S64: {
2505 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(
2506 evaluated_[compare],
2507 Compare<int64>(compare->shape(), opcode, lhs_literal, rhs_literal));
2508 } break;
2509 case F16:
2510 return Unimplemented("unhandled primitive type: F16.");
2511 case F32: {
2512 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(
2513 evaluated_[compare],
2514 Compare<float>(compare->shape(), opcode, lhs_literal, rhs_literal));
2515 } break;
2516 case F64: {
2517 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(
2518 evaluated_[compare],
2519 Compare<double>(compare->shape(), opcode, lhs_literal, rhs_literal));
2520 } break;
2521 case C64: {
2522 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(evaluated_[compare],
2523 Compare<complex64>(compare->shape(), opcode,
2524 lhs_literal, rhs_literal));
2525 } break;
2526 default:
2527 LOG(FATAL) << "HandleCompare: unknown primitive type: "
2528 << PrimitiveType_Name(lhs->shape().element_type());
2529 }
2530
2531 return Status::OK();
2532}
2533
2534Status HloEvaluator::HandleTuple(HloInstruction* tuple) {
2535 std::vector<const Literal*> operand_literals;
2536 for (auto operand : tuple->operands()) {
2537 operand_literals.push_back(&GetEvaluatedLiteralFor(operand));
2538 }
2539
2540 evaluated_[tuple] = Literal::MakeTuple(operand_literals);
2541 return Status::OK();
2542}
2543
2544// Returns an ShapeUtil::IndexIterationSpace that iterates over the output
2545// gather dimensions while keeping the rest of the output dimensions clamped to
2546// 0.
2547ShapeUtil::IndexIterationSpace IterationSpaceForOutputGatherIndices(
2548 const Shape& output_shape, const GatherDimensionNumbers& dim_numbers) {
2549 int64 output_rank = output_shape.dimensions_size();
2550 std::vector<int64> index_base(output_rank, 0);
2551 std::vector<int64> index_count;
2552 index_count.reserve(output_rank);
2553 for (int64 i = 0; i < output_rank; i++) {
2554 bool is_output_gather_dim =
2555 !c_binary_search(dim_numbers.output_window_dims(), i);
2556 index_count.push_back(is_output_gather_dim ? output_shape.dimensions(i)
2557 : 1);
2558 }
2559
2560 return {std::move(index_base), std::move(index_count),
2561 std::vector<int64>(output_rank, 1)};
2562}
2563
2564// Return an ShapeUtil::IndexIterationSpace that iterates over the output window
2565// dimensions while keeping the rest of the output dimensions clamped to 0.
2566ShapeUtil::IndexIterationSpace IterationSpaceForOutputWindowIndices(
2567 int64 output_rank, ArraySlice<int64> window_bounds,
2568 const GatherDimensionNumbers& dim_numbers) {
2569 std::vector<int64> index_base(output_rank, 0);
2570 std::vector<int64> index_count(output_rank, 1);
2571 int64 window_bounds_idx = 0;
2572 for (int64 i = 0; i < output_rank; i++) {
2573 bool is_output_window_dim =
2574 c_binary_search(dim_numbers.output_window_dims(), i);
2575 if (is_output_window_dim) {
2576 while (c_binary_search(dim_numbers.elided_window_dims(),
2577 window_bounds_idx)) {
2578 window_bounds_idx++;
2579 }
2580 index_count[i] = window_bounds[window_bounds_idx++];
2581 }
2582 }
2583
2584 return {std::move(index_base), std::move(index_count),
2585 std::vector<int64>(output_rank, 1)};
2586}
2587
2588// This functor computes the contribution of gather_indices to an input index
2589// corresponding to an output index. That is, given an output index I, it picks
2590// out the gather output indices in I and uses them to look up a gather index,
2591// G, from the gather indices tensor, and expands G into the input space
2592// according to gather_dims_to_operand_dims.
2593class OutputGatherIndexToInputIndex {
2594 public:
2595 // The constructor does some setup work that is amortized across all
2596 // iterations.
2597 explicit OutputGatherIndexToInputIndex(
2598 const GatherDimensionNumbers* dim_numbers, const Shape& input_shape,
2599 const Shape& output_shape, const Literal* gather_indices)
2600 : dim_numbers_(*dim_numbers), gather_indices_(*gather_indices) {
2601 for (int64 i = 0; i < output_shape.dimensions_size(); i++) {
2602 output_dim_is_gather_dims_.push_back(
2603 !c_binary_search(dim_numbers_.output_window_dims(), i));
2604 }
2605
2606 for (int64 i = 0; i < input_shape.dimensions_size(); i++) {
2607 int64 index_of_input_dim_in_index_vector =
2608 std::distance(dim_numbers_.gather_dims_to_operand_dims().begin(),
2609 c_find(dim_numbers_.gather_dims_to_operand_dims(), i));
2610 if (index_of_input_dim_in_index_vector ==
2611 dim_numbers_.gather_dims_to_operand_dims_size()) {
2612 input_dim_value_to_index_vector_.push_back(-1);
2613 } else {
2614 input_dim_value_to_index_vector_.push_back(
2615 index_of_input_dim_in_index_vector);
2616 }
2617 }
2618
2619 index_vector_index_.resize(gather_indices_.shape().dimensions_size());
2620 input_index_.resize(input_shape.dimensions_size());
2621 int64 index_vector_size =
2622 gather_indices_.shape().dimensions(dim_numbers_.index_vector_dim());
2623 index_vector_.resize(index_vector_size);
2624 }
2625
2626 // Returns the contribution of gather_indices to the input index corresponding
2627 // to output_index. See gather_inner_loop_body.
2628 //
2629 // This is conceptually a stateless transformation from output_index to the
2630 // gather input index, but:
2631 //
2632 // - Instead of allocating memory to represent the gather input index on
2633 // every invocation we reuse the same storage for the result
2634 // (input_index_), mutating it in place.
2635 // - Instead of allocating buffers for temporary values like
2636 // index_vector_index_ and index_vector on every invocation, we reuse the
2637 // same storage for all invocations.
2638 //
2639 // This returns an arrayslice into memory owned by the class.
2640 StatusOr<ArraySlice<int64>> operator()(ArraySlice<int64> output_index) {
2641 PropagateOutputIndexGatherDimsToIndexVectorIndex(output_index);
2642 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(FetchIndexVector());
2643 PropagateIndexVectorToInputIndex();
2644 return ArraySlice<int64>(input_index_);
2645 }
2646
2647 private:
2648 // Propagates the gather index dimensions from the output index into
2649 // index_vector_index_ by mutating index_vector_index_ in place. Does not
2650 // update the dim_numbers.index_vector_dim() dimension -- that's the dimension
2651 // we iterate over in FetchIndexVector.
2652 void PropagateOutputIndexGatherDimsToIndexVectorIndex(
2653 ArraySlice<int64> output_index) {
2654 int64 index_vector_index_i = 0;
2655 for (int64 i = 0, e = output_index.size(); i < e; i++) {
2656 if (!output_dim_is_gather_dims_[i]) {
2657 continue;
2658 }
2659
2660 if (index_vector_index_i == dim_numbers_.index_vector_dim()) {
2661 index_vector_index_i++;
2662 }
2663
2664 index_vector_index_[index_vector_index_i++] = output_index[i];
2665 }
2666 }
2667
2668 // Populates index_vector_ by iterating over gather_indices_ according to
2669 // index_vector_index_.
2670 Status FetchIndexVector() {
2671 int64 index_vector_dim = dim_numbers_.index_vector_dim();
2672 for (int64 i = 0, e = index_vector_.size(); i < e; i++) {
2673 index_vector_index_[index_vector_dim] = i;
2674 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(index_vector_[i], gather_indices_.GetIntegralAsS64(
2675 index_vector_index_));
2676 }
2677 return Status::OK();
2678 }
2679
2680 // Populates input_index_.
2681 void PropagateIndexVectorToInputIndex() {
2682 for (int64 i = 0, e = input_index_.size(); i < e; i++) {
2683 if (input_dim_value_to_index_vector_[i] != -1) {
2684 input_index_[i] = index_vector_[input_dim_value_to_index_vector_[i]];
2685 }
2686
2687 // If input_dim_value_to_index_vector_[i] == -1 then input_index_[i]
2688 // remains 0, as set by the constructor.
2689 }
2690 }
2691
2692 // input_dim_value_to_index_vector_[i] tells us how to compute dimension i of
2693 // the input index from the index vector. See
2694 // PropagateIndexVectorToInputIndex.
2695 std::vector<int64> input_dim_value_to_index_vector_;
2696
2697 // output_dim_is_gather_dims_[i] is true iff the output index i is a gather
2698 // dimension.
2699 std::vector<bool> output_dim_is_gather_dims_;
2700
2701 // The buffer into which we construct an index into gather_indices_ to fetch
2702 // the index vector.
2703 std::vector<int64> index_vector_index_;
2704
2705 // The index vector fetched from gather_indices_.
2706 std::vector<int64> index_vector_;
2707
2708 // The result computed by this functor. operator() returns an ArraySlice into
2709 // this vector.
2710 std::vector<int64> input_index_;
2711
2712 const GatherDimensionNumbers& dim_numbers_;
2713 const Literal& gather_indices_;
2714};
2715
2716// This functor computes the contribution of the window indices in an output
2717// index to an input index. That is, given an output index I it picks out the
2718// output window indices in I and expands it into a window index into the input
2719// shape.
2720class OutputWindowIndexToInputIndex {
2721 public:
2722 // The constructor does some setup work that is amortized across all
2723 // iterations.
2724 explicit OutputWindowIndexToInputIndex(
2725 const GatherDimensionNumbers& dim_numbers, const Shape& input_shape,
2726 const Shape& output_shape) {
2727 std::vector<int64> window_index_to_output_index;
2728 int64 output_index_count = 0;
2729 for (int64 i = 0; i < output_shape.dimensions_size(); i++) {
2730 if (c_binary_search(dim_numbers.output_window_dims(), i)) {
2731 window_index_to_output_index.push_back(output_index_count++);
2732 } else {
2733 output_index_count++;
2734 }
2735 }
2736
2737 int64 window_dim_count = 0;
2738 for (int64 i = 0; i < input_shape.dimensions_size(); i++) {
2739 if (c_binary_search(dim_numbers.elided_window_dims(), i)) {
2740 input_dim_value_to_output_index_.push_back(-1);
2741 } else {
2742 input_dim_value_to_output_index_.push_back(
2743 window_index_to_output_index[window_dim_count++]);
2744 }
2745 }
2746
2747 input_index_.resize(input_shape.dimensions_size());
2748 }
2749
2750 // Returns the contribution of the window indices to the input index
2751 // corresponding to output_index. See gather_inner_loop_body.
2752 //
2753 // This is conceptually a stateless transformation from output_index to the
2754 // window input index, but instead of allocating memory to represent the
2755 // gather input index on every invocation we reuse the same storage for the
2756 // result (input_index_), mutating it in place.
2757 //
2758 // This returns an arrayslice into memory owned by the class.
2759 StatusOr<ArraySlice<int64>> operator()(ArraySlice<int64> output_index) {
2760 PropagateOutputIndexWindowDimsToInputIndex(output_index);
2761 return ArraySlice<int64>(input_index_);
2762 }
2763
2764 private:
2765 // Propagates window dimensions from the output index to input_index_ by
2766 // mutating input_index_ in place.
2767 void PropagateOutputIndexWindowDimsToInputIndex(
2768 ArraySlice<int64> output_index) {
2769 for (int64 i = 0, e = input_index_.size(); i < e; i++) {
2770 if (input_dim_value_to_output_index_[i] != -1) {
2771 input_index_[i] = output_index[input_dim_value_to_output_index_[i]];
2772 }
2773
2774 // If input_dim_value_to_index_vector_[i] == -1 then input_index_[i]
2775 // remains 0, as set by the constructor.
2776 }
2777 }
2778
2779 // input_dim_value_to_index_vector_[i] tells us how to compute dimension i of
2780 // the input index from the output index. See
2781 // PropagateOutputIndexToInputIndex.
2782 std::vector<int64> input_dim_value_to_output_index_;
2783
2784 // The result computed by this functor. operator() returns an ArraySlice into
2785 // this vector.
2786 std::vector<int64> input_index_;
2787};
2788
2789// Rehapes the gather indices input to have a trailing degenerate `1` dimension
2790// if necessary. Hands over the ownership of the newly created literal (if
2791// there is one) to `reshaped_gather_indices`.
2792static StatusOr<std::reference_wrapper<const Literal>> ReshapedGatherIndices(
2793 int64 index_vector_dim, const Literal& gather_indices,
2794 std::unique_ptr<Literal>* reshaped_gather_indices) {
2795 if (gather_indices.shape().dimensions_size() != index_vector_dim) {
2796 return std::cref(gather_indices);
2797 }
2798
2799 std::vector<int64> new_shape(gather_indices.shape().dimensions().begin(),
2800 gather_indices.shape().dimensions().end());
2801 new_shape.push_back(1);
2802 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(*reshaped_gather_indices,
2803 gather_indices.Reshape(new_shape));
2804 return std::cref(**reshaped_gather_indices);
2805}
2806
2807Status HloEvaluator::HandleGather(HloInstruction* gather) {
2808 std::unique_ptr<Literal> result = Literal::CreateFromShape(gather->shape());
2809 const Shape& shape = gather->shape();
2810 const GatherDimensionNumbers& dim_numbers =
2811 gather->gather_dimension_numbers();
2812 const Literal& operand = GetEvaluatedLiteralFor(gather->operand(0));
2813 std::unique_ptr<Literal> reshaped_gather_indices;
2814 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(
2815 const Literal& gather_indices,
2816 ReshapedGatherIndices(dim_numbers.index_vector_dim(),
2817 GetEvaluatedLiteralFor(gather->operand(1)),
2818 &reshaped_gather_indices));
2819
2820 // We iterate over the gather dimensions in the output shape in an outer loop
2821 // nest, and iterate over the window dimensions in the output shape in an
2822 // inner loop nest.
2823
2824 ShapeUtil::IndexIterationSpace gather_indices_iteration_space =
2825 IterationSpaceForOutputGatherIndices(shape, dim_numbers);
2826 ShapeUtil::IndexIterationSpace window_indices_iteration_space =
2827 IterationSpaceForOutputWindowIndices(
2828 shape.dimensions_size(), gather->gather_window_bounds(), dim_numbers);
2829
2830 // Scratch buffers that hold an index in the output shape and the
2831 // corresponding index in the input shape.
2832 std::vector<int64> input_index(operand.shape().dimensions_size());
2833 std::vector<int64> output_index(gather->shape().dimensions_size());
2834
2835 OutputGatherIndexToInputIndex output_gather_index_to_input_index(
2836 &gather->gather_dimension_numbers(), /*input_shape=*/operand.shape(),
2837 /*output_shape=*/shape, &gather_indices);
2838 OutputWindowIndexToInputIndex output_window_index_to_input_index(
2839 gather->gather_dimension_numbers(), /*input_shape=*/operand.shape(),
2840 /*output_shape=*/shape);
2841
2842 const Shape& operand_shape = operand.shape();
2843
2844 auto gather_inner_loop_body =
2845 [&](ArraySlice<int64> output_window_index,
2846 ArraySlice<int64> input_gather_index,
2847 ArraySlice<int64> output_gather_index) -> StatusOr<bool> {
2848 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(
2849 ArraySlice<int64> input_window_index,
2850 output_window_index_to_input_index(output_window_index));
2851 for (int i = 0, e = output_index.size(); i < e; i++) {
2852 output_index[i] = output_gather_index[i] + output_window_index[i];
2853 DCHECK_LT(output_index[i], shape.dimensions(i));
2854 }
2855 for (int i = 0, e = input_index.size(); i < e; i++) {
2856 // TODO(b/74360564): We should implement whatever out of bounds behavior
2857 // we decide for dynamic-slice here as well.
2858 input_index[i] = (input_gather_index[i] + input_window_index[i]) %
2859 operand_shape.dimensions(i);
2860 if (input_index[i] < 0) {
2861 input_index[i] += operand_shape.dimensions(i);
2862 }
2863 }
2864 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
2865 result->CopyElementFrom(operand, input_index, output_index));
2866 return true;
2867 };
2868
2869 auto gather_outer_loop_body =
2870 [&](ArraySlice<int64> output_gather_index) -> StatusOr<bool> {
2871 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(
2872 ArraySlice<int64> input_gather_index,
2873 output_gather_index_to_input_index(output_gather_index));
2874 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(ShapeUtil::ForEachIndexWithStatus(
2875 shape, window_indices_iteration_space,
2876 std::bind(gather_inner_loop_body, std::placeholders::_1,
2877 input_gather_index, output_gather_index)));
2878 return true;
2879 };
2880
2881 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(ShapeUtil::ForEachIndexWithStatus(
2882 shape, gather_indices_iteration_space, gather_outer_loop_body));
2883 evaluated_[gather] = std::move(result);
2884 return Status::OK();
2885}
2886
2887Status HloEvaluator::HandleGetTupleElement(HloInstruction* get_tuple_element) {
2888 const auto result_shape = get_tuple_element->shape();
2889 const int64 index = get_tuple_element->tuple_index();
2890
2891 auto operand = get_tuple_element->operand(0);
2892 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(
2893 auto inferred_return_shape,
2894 ShapeInference::InferGetTupleElementShape(operand->shape(), index));
2895 TF_RET_CHECK(ShapeUtil::Compatible(result_shape, inferred_return_shape))
2896 << "return shape set to: " << ShapeUtil::HumanString(result_shape)
2897 << " but is inferred to be: "
2898 << ShapeUtil::HumanString(inferred_return_shape);
2899
2900 const Literal& operand_tuple_literal = GetEvaluatedLiteralFor(operand);
2901
2902 evaluated_[get_tuple_element] = MakeUnique<Literal>(
2903 ShapeUtil::GetTupleElementShape(operand->shape(), index));
2904 return evaluated_[get_tuple_element]->CopyFrom(operand_tuple_literal,
2905 /*dest_shape_index=*/{},
2906 /*src_shape_index=*/{index});
2907}
2908
2909Status HloEvaluator::HandleCopy(HloInstruction* copy) {
2910 TF_RET_CHECK(ShapeUtil::Compatible(copy->shape(), copy->operand(0)->shape()));
2911
2912 auto result = GetEvaluatedLiteralFor(copy->operand(0)).CloneToUnique();
2913 evaluated_[copy] = std::move(result);
2914 return Status::OK();
2915}
2916
2917Status HloEvaluator::HandleCall(HloInstruction* call) {
2918 auto* computation = call->to_apply();
2919 auto operands = call->operands();
2920
2921 std::vector<const Literal*> arg_literals;
2922 arg_literals.reserve(operands.size());
2923 for (auto operand : operands) {
2924 const Literal& arg_literal = GetEvaluatedLiteralFor(operand);
2925 arg_literals.push_back(&arg_literal);
2926 }
2927
2928 HloEvaluator embedded_evaluator;
2929 std::unique_ptr<Literal> result =
2930 embedded_evaluator.Evaluate<const Literal*>(*computation, arg_literals)
2931 .ConsumeValueOrDie();
2932
2933 evaluated_[call] = std::move(result);
2934 return Status::OK();
2935}
2936
2937Status HloEvaluator::HandleFusion(HloInstruction* fusion) {
2938 // Attach cloned computation to an empty HLO module so the existing ones are
2939 // not modified.
2940 HloModule empty_hlo_module("EmptyModuleForFusion");
2941 auto cloned_fused_computation =
2942 fusion->fused_instructions_computation()->Clone(
2943 /*suffix=*/"clone_with_layout", &empty_hlo_module);
2944 for (auto* instruction : cloned_fused_computation->instructions()) {
2945 LayoutUtil::SetToDefaultLayout(instruction->mutable_shape());
2946 }
2947 auto readded_computation =
2948 empty_hlo_module.AddEntryComputation(std::move(cloned_fused_computation));
2949
2950 auto operands = fusion->operands();
2951 std::vector<const Literal*> arg_literals;
2952 arg_literals.reserve(operands.size());
2953 for (auto operand : operands) {
2954 const Literal& arg_literal = GetEvaluatedLiteralFor(operand);
2955 arg_literals.push_back(&arg_literal);
2956 }
2957
2958 HloEvaluator embedded_evaluator;
2959 std::unique_ptr<Literal> result =
2960 embedded_evaluator
2961 .Evaluate<const Literal*>(*readded_computation, arg_literals)
2962 .ConsumeValueOrDie();
2963
2964 evaluated_[fusion] = std::move(result);
2965 return Status::OK();
2966}
2967
2968Status HloEvaluator::HandleConditional(HloInstruction* conditional) {
2969 const auto& pred = GetEvaluatedLiteralFor(conditional->operand(0));
2970 const auto& true_computation_arg =
2971 GetEvaluatedLiteralFor(conditional->operand(1));
2972 const auto& false_computation_arg =
2973 GetEvaluatedLiteralFor(conditional->operand(2));
2974
2975 auto* true_computation = conditional->true_computation();
2976 auto* false_computation = conditional->false_computation();
2977
2978 auto result = Literal::CreateFromShape(conditional->shape());
2979 HloEvaluator embedded_evaluator;
2980 if (pred.Get<bool>({})) {
2981 result = embedded_evaluator
2982 .Evaluate<const Literal*>(*true_computation,
2983 {&true_computation_arg})
2984 .ConsumeValueOrDie();
2985 } else {
2986 result = embedded_evaluator
2987 .Evaluate<const Literal*>(*false_computation,
2988 {&false_computation_arg})
2989 .ConsumeValueOrDie();
2990 }
2991
2992 evaluated_[conditional] = std::move(result);
2993 return Status::OK();
2994}
2995
2996Status HloEvaluator::HandleSelect(HloInstruction* select) {
2997 const auto& pred = GetEvaluatedLiteralFor(select->operand(0));
2998 const auto& on_true = GetEvaluatedLiteralFor(select->operand(1));
2999 const auto& on_false = GetEvaluatedLiteralFor(select->operand(2));
3000
3001 // If predicate is of scalar type, no element-wise selection would be needed.
3002 // This would also handle output array of tuple types as the DefaultAction
3003 // would go through the TypedVisitor which doesn't handle tuples.
3004 if (ShapeUtil::IsScalar(pred.shape())) {
3005 if (pred.Get<bool>({})) {
3006 evaluated_[select] = on_true.CloneToUnique();
3007 } else {
3008 evaluated_[select] = on_false.CloneToUnique();
3009 }
3010 return Status::OK();
3011 }
3012
3013 return DefaultAction(select);
3014}
3015
3016Status HloEvaluator::HandleWhile(HloInstruction* while_hlo) {
3017 HloComputation* cond_comp = while_hlo->while_condition();
3018 HloComputation* body_comp = while_hlo->while_body();
3019 // Initialize the loop carried valued with the input to the While instruction.
3020 auto lcv = GetEvaluatedLiteralFor(while_hlo->operand(0)).CloneToUnique();
3021 bool keep_going = true;
3022 int64 iteration_count = 0;
3023 HloEvaluator cond_evaluator(max_loop_iterations_);
3024 HloEvaluator loop_body_evaluator(max_loop_iterations_);
3025 while (keep_going) {
3026 if (max_loop_iterations_ >= 0 && iteration_count++ > max_loop_iterations_) {
3027 return InvalidArgument("Loop %s exceeded loop iteration limit (%lld).",
3028 while_hlo->name().c_str(), max_loop_iterations_);
3029 }
3030 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(auto cond_val, cond_evaluator.Evaluate<Literal*>(
3031 *cond_comp, {lcv.get()}));
3032 keep_going = cond_val->GetFirstElement<bool>();
3033 if (keep_going) {
3034 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(auto body_val, loop_body_evaluator.Evaluate<Literal*>(
3035 *body_comp, {lcv.get()}));
3036 VLOG(3) << "Loop iteration result: " << body_val->ToString();
3037 lcv = std::move(body_val);
3038 cond_evaluator.ResetVisitStates();
3039 loop_body_evaluator.ResetVisitStates();
3040 }
3041 }
3042 evaluated_[while_hlo] = std::move(lcv);
3043 return Status::OK();
3044}
3045
3046Status HloEvaluator::Preprocess(HloInstruction* hlo) {
3047 VLOG(2) << "About to visit HLO: " << hlo->ToString();
3048 return Status::OK();
3049}

3051Status HloEvaluator::Postprocess(HloInstruction* hlo) {
3052 VLOG(2) << "Finished visiting " << hlo->ToString()
3053 << "; evaluated value is: " << GetEvaluatedLiteralFor(hlo).ToString();
3054 return Status::OK();
3055}
